{"type":"message","id":"0974a30c","parentId":"50801da8","timestamp":"2026-04-14T14:25:59.403Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see the full picture. Let me check if hooks are actually enabled in the config, and look at the hook registration mechanism.\n\nThe handler.js is the bootstrap hook that:\n1. Listens for `agent:bootstrap` events\n2. Injects self-improvement reminder\n3. Reads latest `*-session-summary.md` from memory/ and injects it\n\nBut the hook itself needs to be registered. Let me check how hooks are enabled/registered in OpenClaw.","thinkingSignature":"ad29af7e41ac2631e4abf18abdb8091d1480f24bb614be385c5495863fdcd65f"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_f40bfcc74f5346259e8e6f8c","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw hooks list 2>/dev/null; echo \"---\"; cat ~/.openclaw/config/hooks.json 2>/dev/null"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_b16042325fa64071b05da317","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"find ~/.openclaw -name \"hook*.json\" -o -name \"hooks.json\" 2>/dev/null | xargs cat 2>/dev/null; ls ~/.openclaw/hooks/ 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1012,"output":213,"cacheRead":26560,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":27785,"cost":{"input":0.0003036,"output":0.0002556,"cacheRead":0.0015936,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0021528}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776176753958,"responseId":"062d817173f9e5be708d4ec2fc4a0773"}}
