{"type":"message","id":"323db58e","parentId":"c789c7a0","timestamp":"2026-04-14T14:26:55.508Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see a critical issue! The `session-summary` hook's `run()` function has:\n\n```javascript\nconst isTarget = event.type === \"command\" && (event.action === \"new\" || event.action === \"reset\");\n```\n\nBut the `handler.js` (the bootstrap hook) has:\n```javascript\nif (event.type !== \"agent\" || event.action !== \"bootstrap\") {\n    return;\n}\n```\n\nSo the session-summary hook listens for `command new/reset`, while the bootstrap hook listens for `agent bootstrap`. These might be different event types!\n\nAlso the ephemeral directory is empty (0 lines in jsonl files), which confirms the ephemeral capture isn't working either.\n\n\nLet me look at how the gateway is actually firing these events to understand the disconnect.","thinkingSignature":"648b9d02af5fbd563117678887ca64daaff987b53c063c10e91e9b2621efba49"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_ee0dc72999ea4379a2b4b55e","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls ~/.openclaw/memory/ephemeral/ 2>/dev/null; find ~/.openclaw/agents/main -name \"*.jsonl\" 2>/dev/null | head -5; ls ~/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/ 2>/dev/null | head -10"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_b7dd079f2f7b48539935c2b9","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/hooks/session-summary/handler.js | grep -A5 \"isTarget\\|type.*command\\|event.type\" | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":231,"output":291,"cacheRead":36096,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":36618,"cost":{"input":0.00006929999999999999,"output":0.0003492,"cacheRead":0.0021657599999999996,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0025842599999999997}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776176809497,"responseId":"062d81a9e993cef99928fcde5da1ba55"}}
