{"type":"message","id":"484af106","parentId":"43c498a8","timestamp":"2026-04-14T14:27:04.738Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the issue clearly! The session-summary hook checks for `event.type === \"command\"` and `event.action === \"new\"`. But the gateway hooks system sends events with different types. Let me check what event type is actually sent for /new commands.\n\nLooking at the auto-score-classify hook - it's also in the same hooks directory. Let me check what event type it receives.\n\nAlso, the ephemeral dir is EMPTY - there are no files in it. So even if the session-summary hook ran, it would just produce a fallback summary with no ephemeral data.\n\nThe core issue is clear now:\n1. `session-summary` hook checks `event.type === \"command\"` → this might not match what gateway sends\n\n\n2. The ephemeral directory has no data at all, so there's nothing to work with\n3. The bootstrap hook that should inject session-summary files into context isn't creating those files in the first place\n\nI need to verify what event type the gateway actually sends for /new commands, and check whether the auto-score-classify hook is functioning properly since classification data should be flowing through it.","thinkingSignature":"cb5f32bb468554cfc1ed30fdf09fc304a91e3d67a9d61c3659b082511aef8ada"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_3a1c813ba78f4fe9941e37d3","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/hooks/auto-score-classify/handler.js 2>/dev/null | head -50"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_013c5e70ed2643fb862155ac","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls ~/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/*.jsonl 2>/dev/null | grep -v reset | grep -v checkpoint | head -5"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1004,"output":320,"cacheRead":36288,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":37612,"cost":{"input":0.0003012,"output":0.000384,"cacheRead":0.0021772799999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0028