{"type":"message","id":"54134323","parentId":"c21aa377","timestamp":"2026-04-14T14:27:15.030Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the issue clearly:\n\n1. **session-summary hook** checks `event.type === \"command\" && (event.action === \"new\" || event.action === \"reset\")` - it fires on COMMAND events (from on-message.sh)\n\n2. **auto-score-classify hook** fires on every inbound message - it works (we saw context.json populated with classification/scoring)\n\n3. **handler.js (bootstrap hook)** fires on `agent:bootstrap` events and injects session summary into bootstrapFiles\n\nThe issue: session-summary hook needs to see a `command` type event, but it's not clear if/when that event fires. \n\nLet me trace through what happens when a `/new` command comes in - there's an on-message.sh hook that might intercept it first, then session-summary checks for that command event type. But I'm not seeing where the event actually gets emitted when the user triggers `/new`.\n\nThe gateway logs would tell me if any of these hooks are even firing, but they're empty. Let me check the actual session files instead to see what data's being stored. I found a reset file from today at 05:01 - that's the most recent one. So the session-summary hook isn't creating anything when it should be. The ephemeral directory exists but has no data, which means auto-score-classify isn't running either. That hook requires a meaningful message, and this is just a command event, so it was correctly filtered out. But this reveals the real problem: session-summary isn't triggering at all, and there are no ephemeral entries being captured.","thinkingSignature":"01dfe7e98e49bc649a126dc51d1f236ad63b9b766d3ac8e21ba9dd37b7a7868e"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_711bf733c5704bdba8d34a7d","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/hooks/on-message.sh 2>/dev/null"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_115109d4eeba4fed8ac495d2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"find ~/.openclaw/hooks -name \"*.json\" -o -name \"event*\" 2>/dev/null | xargs cat 2>/dev/null | head -50"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":716,"output":410,"cacheRead":37248,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":38374,"cost":{"input":0.0002148,"output":0.0004919999999999999,"cacheRead":0.00223488,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00294168}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776176824900,"responseId":"062d81b8decab047653386d6286926e2"}}
{"type":"message","id":"2f240b63","parentId":"54134323","timestamp":"2026-04-14T14:27:15.163Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_711bf733c5704bdba8d34a7d","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/bin/bash\n# OpenClaw Context Hook - HTTP 版本\n# 将消息发送到保护层的 HTTP 服务\n\nMESSAGE=\"${OPENCLAW_MESSAGE:-}\"\nUSER=\"${OPENCLAW_SENDER:-unknown}\"\nCHANNEL=\"${OPENCLAW_CHANNEL:-unknown}\"\nSERVER_URL=\"http://127.0.0.1:3101\"\n\nif [ -n \"$MESSAGE\" ]; then\n  # 发送到 Context API（openclaw-router）\n  curl -s -X POST \"${SERVER_URL}/api/context\" \\\n    -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n    -d \"{\\\"role\\\":\\\"user\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"$(echo \"$MESSAGE\" | jq -Rs .)\\\",\\\"user\\\":\\\"$USER\\\",\\\"channel\\\":\\\"$CHANNEL\\\"}\" \\\n    > /dev/null 2>&1 || true\nfi"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":76,"aggregated":"#!/bin/bash\n# OpenClaw Context Hook - HTTP 版本\n# 将消息发送到保护层的 HTTP 服务\n\nMESSAGE=\"${OPENCLAW_MESSAGE:-}\"\nUSER=\"${OPENCLAW_SENDER:-unknown}\"\nCHANNEL=\"${OPENCLAW_CHANNEL:-unknown}\"\nSERVER_URL=\"http://127.0.0.1:3101\"\n\nif [ -n \"$MESSAGE\" ]; then\n  # 发送到 Context API（openclaw-router）\n  curl -s -X POST \"${SERVER_URL}/api/context\" \\\n    -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n    -d \"{\\\"role\\\":\\\"user\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"$(echo \"$MESSAGE\" | jq -Rs .)\\\",\\\"user\\\":\\\"$USER\\\",\\\"channel\\\":\\\"$CHANNEL\\\"}\" \\\n    > /dev/null 2>&1 || true\nfi","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776176835150}}
