{"type":"message","id":"311da2be","parentId":"280104c7","timestamp":"2026-04-14T14:27:22.181Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see it! `on-message.sh` sends messages to port 3101 (the openclaw-router/context-api that we disabled). But we killed that service. However, this script runs when messages are sent - but it's not the session-summary hook.\n\nLet me think about the actual event flow for `/new`:\n\nFrom the `session-summary/handler.js`:\n```javascript\nconst isTarget = event.type === \"command\" && (event.action === \"new\" || event.action === \"reset\");\n```\n\nSo it listens for `type=command, action=new`. But the auto-score-classify hook in the same file also has its own event filtering.\n\n\nI need to understand how these hooks are actually triggered - are they defined in a config file somewhere that tells the gateway which events to listen for? Let me trace through the hook configuration itself.","thinkingSignature":"253c7d2c4dc287f148e706b73fccb4a98e2335de05c47bf3f1e812afbadd8489"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_d32fc8efa08b4f4ea99e1e61","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/hooks/handler.ts 2>/dev/null | head -50"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_c3d6a17e245645369de9862b","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw hooks list 2>&1; echo \"---\"; cat ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json | python3 -c \"import json,sys; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print(json.dumps(d.get('hooks', {}), indent=2))\" 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":293,"output":290,"cacheRead":37952,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":38535,"cost":{"input":0.0000879,"output":0.000348,"cacheRead":0.0022771199999999997,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0027130199999999996}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776176835174,"responseId":"062d81c2faf3215d6002ed00ae429eb6"}}
{"type":"message","id":"a7ffd399","parentId":"311da2be","timestamp":"2026-04-14T14:27:22.297Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_d32fc8efa08b4f4ea99e1e61","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"/**\n * Self-Improvement + Session-Summary Bootstrap Hook for OpenClaw\n *\n * Injects:\n * 1. Self-Improvement reminder during agent bootstrap\n * 2. Previous session's summary (memory/*-session-summary.md) as bootstrap context\n *\n * Fires on agent:bootstrap event before workspace files are injected.\n */\n\nimport fs from 'node:fs';\nimport path from 'node:path';\nimport os from 'node:os';\nimport type { HookHandler } from 'openclaw/hooks';\n\nconst SELF_IMPROVEMENT_REMINDER = `## Self-Improvement Reminder\n\nAfter completing tasks, evaluate if any learnings should be captured:\n\n**Log when:**\n- User corrects you → \\`.learnings/LEARNINGS.md\\`\n- Command/operation fails → \\`.learnings/ERRORS.md\\`\n- User wants missing capability → \\`.learnings/FEATURE_REQUESTS.md\\`\n- You discover your knowledge was wrong → \\`.learnings/LEARNINGS.md\\`\n- You find a better approach → \\`.learnings/LEARNINGS.md\\`\n\n**Promote when pattern is proven:**\n- Behavioral patterns → \\`SOUL.md\\`\n- Workflow improvements → \\`AGENTS.md\\`\n- Tool gotchas → \\`TOOLS.md\\`\n\nKeep entries simple: date, title, what happened, what to do differently.`;\n\n/**\n * Find and read the most recent session-summary file.\n * Looks in memory/ for *-session-summary.md files, returns most recent by mtime.\n */\nasync function getLatestSessionSummary(): Promise<string | null> {\n  try {\n    const memoryDir = path.join(\n      process.env.OPENCLAW_WORKSPACE_DIR || path.join(os.homedir(), '.openclaw', 'workspace'),\n      'memory'\n    );\n\n    const files = await fs.promises.readdir(memoryDir);\n    const summaryFiles = files.filter(f => f.endsWith('-session-summary.md'));\n\n    if (summaryFiles.length === 0) return null;\n\n    // Sort by mtime descending"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":67,"aggregated":"/**\n * Self-Improvement + Session-Summary Bootstrap Hook for OpenClaw\n *\n * Injects:\n * 1. Self-Improvement reminder during agent bootstrap\n * 2. Previous session's summary (memory/*-session-summary.md) as bootstrap context\n *\n * Fires on agent:bootstrap event before workspace files are injected.\n */\n\nimport fs from 'node:fs';\nimport path from 'node:path';\nimport os from 'node:os';\nimport type { HookHandler } from 'openclaw/hooks';\n\nconst SELF_IMPROVEMENT_REMINDER = `## Self-Improvement Reminder\n\nAfter completing tasks, evaluate if any learnings should be captured:\n\n**Log when:**\n- User corrects you → \\`.learnings/LEARNINGS.md\\`\n- Command/operation fails → \\`.learnings/ERRORS.md\\`\n- User wants missing capability → \\`.learnings/FEATURE_REQUESTS.md\\`\n- You discover your knowledge was wrong → \\`.learnings/LEARNINGS.md\\`\n- You find a better approach → \\`.learnings/LEARNINGS.md\\`\n\n**Promote when pattern is proven:**\n- Behavioral patterns → \\`SOUL.md\\`\n- Workflow improvements → \\`AGENTS.md\\`\n- Tool gotchas → \\`TOOLS.md\\`\n\nKeep entries simple: date, title, what happened, what to do differently.`;\n\n/**\n * Find and read the most recent session-summary file.\n * Looks in memory/ for *-session-summary.md files, returns most recent by mtime.\n */\nasync function getLatestSessionSummary(): Promise<string | null> {\n  try {\n    const memoryDir = path.join(\n      process.env.OPENCLAW_WORKSPACE_DIR || path.join(os.homedir(), '.openclaw', 'workspace'),\n      'memory'\n    );\n\n    const files = await fs.promises.readdir(memoryDir);\n    const summaryFiles = files.filter(f => f.endsWith('-session-summary.md'));\n\n    if (summaryFiles.length === 0) return null;\n\n    // Sort by mtime descending","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776176842285}}
{"type":"message","id":"ca8c2286","parentId":"a7ffd399","timestamp":"2026-04-14T14:27:22.316Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_c3d6a17e245645369de9862b","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"/bin/bash: openclaw: command not found\n---\n{\n  \"internal\": {\n    \"enabled\": true,\n    \"entries\": {\n      \"session-memory\": {\n        \"enabled\": true\n      },\n      \"command-logger\": {\n        \"enabled\": true\n      },\n      \"self-improvement\": {\n        \"enabled\": true\n      },\n      \"context_hook\": {\n        \"enabled\": true\n      },\n      \"auto-score-classify\": {\n        \"enabled\": true\n      },\n      \"session-summary\": {\n        \"enabled\": true\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":88,"aggregated":"/bin/bash: openclaw: command not found\n---\n{\n  \"internal\": {\n    \"enabled\": true,\n    \"entries\": {\n      \"session-memory\": {\n        \"enabled\": true\n      },\n      \"command-logger\": {\n        \"enabled\": true\n      },\n      \"self-improvement\": {\n        \"enabled\": true\n      },\n      \"context_hook\": {\n        \"enabled\": true\n      },\n      \"auto-score-classify\": {\n        \"enabled\": true\n      },\n      \"session-summary\": {\n        \"enabled\": true\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776176842306}}
{"type":"message","id":"95bd56e7","parentId":"ca8c2286","timestamp":"2026-04-14T14:27:37.077Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have the full picture. Let me analyze the situation:\n\n**The two hooks:**\n\n1. **`session-summary` hook** (handler.js) - fires on `command` + `new/reset`\n2. **`handler.js` (and handler.ts)** - fires on `agent:bootstrap`\n\nBoth are enabled in config. They have different event type filters:\n- session-summary: `event.type === \"command\"`\n- handler.js: `event.type === \"agent\"`\n\nThe issue is: when `/new` is triggered, what event type does OpenClaw actually fire?\n\nFrom the `commands.log` we see `{\"action\":\"new\", ...}` - but the events in the log are from the command-logger hook, which logs the raw action.\n\n\nNow I'm wondering if the bootstrap handler is even being called properly. When a new session starts via `/new`, OpenClaw fires an `agent:bootstrap` event that loads workspace files and runs the handler.js logic to inject bootstrap files. But there's a timing mismatch here - the session-summary handler.js is looking for `event.type === \"command\"` with actions \"new\" or \"reset\", yet the bootstrap handler.js is checking for `event.type === \"agent\"` with action \"bootstrap\". These hooks might be firing at different points in the lifecycle, or the event structure itself might not match what either handler expects. The bootstrap handler is looking for the event structure to have `event.type === \"agent\"`, `event.action === \"bootstrap\"`, and `event.context.bootstrapFiles` as an array. The session-summary hook checks for `event.type === \"command\"` with `new` or `reset` actions instead.\n\nThe webchat session might be triggering events in a different format than what session-summary expects, or the command event itself isn't firing at all. Looking at the commands log, I can see what the actual event structure looks like, which would help clarify why the session-summary handler isn't catching webchat sessions properly. The session-summary hook filters for `event.type === \"command\"` with `event.action === \"new\"`, but based on the command-logger output, the event structure might be different or the hook simply isn't being invoked for webchat sessions. The event structure likely differs between /new and /reset commands, which could explain why the session-summary hook isn't firing. I'm also noticing the session summary files haven't been created despite previous debugging, so there's likely a disconnect between when these events are triggered and when the hook actually runs. Looking at the handler.js logic, it checks for `event.type === \"agent\"` and `event.action === \"bootstrap\"`, but the bootstrap event structure might not include the `bootstrapFiles` array that it's trying to access.\n\nI need to trace where the bootstrap event originates to understand what structure it actually has and why the summary generation isn't triggering.","thinkingSignature":"5d3e526fc15f2dd618ad5dd3e073b1af031305ccae809a9bb8a04efb48187127"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_61eeac01e8f841c1a6181e66","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"find ~/.openclaw -name \"*.js\" -path \"*/hooks/*\" ! -name \"handler.js\" ! -name \"handler.ts\" 2>/dev/null | xargs grep -l \"bootstrap\\|agent:bootstrap\" 2>/dev/null; grep -r \"agent:bootstrap\\|bootstrapFiles\" ~/.openclaw/hooks/ 2>/dev/null | grep -v \".js:\" | head -20"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_e9ca5c7076754554bb8b7809","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"find ~/.openclaw/v8 -name \"*.js\" -not -path \"*/node_modules/*\" 2>/dev/null | head -10; ls ~/.openclaw/v8/ 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":722,"output":750,"cacheRead":38208,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":39680,"cost":{"input":0.00021659999999999998,"output":0.0009,"cacheRead":0.00229248,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00340908}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776176842317,"responseId":"0