{"type":"message","id":"41356124","parentId":"e2da909f","timestamp":"2026-04-14T14:27:47.052Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So the `handler.ts` is the bootstrap hook (the one that injects PREVIOUS_SESSION_SUMMARY). And `handler.js` (in hooks/) also references the same bootstrap hook logic.\n\nNow I see the issue: there are TWO handler files that look like they do the same thing:\n- `~/.openclaw/hooks/handler.js` - ESM, uses `export default`\n- `~/.openclaw/hooks/handler.ts` - TypeScript\n\nAnd then the session-summary hook is at `~/.openclaw/hooks/session-summary/handler.js`.\n\nThe bootstrap hook (`handler.ts`/`handler.js`) checks `event.type !== 'agent' || event.action !== 'bootstrap'`.\n\n\nThe session-summary hook checks `event.type !== 'command' || (event.action !== 'new' && event.action !== 'reset')` — completely different event types. The session-summary hook listens for `command` events while the bootstrap hook listens for `agent` events, so they should theoretically run on different triggers.\n\nBut the real issue is that neither hook appears to be firing at all. There's no session-summary file from this session or any recent session, the ephemeral directory is empty, and the commands.log shows a `/new` was issued at 14:23:48 but the hook never executed. This suggests either the hook configuration is broken or the gateway isn't properly routing events to the hooks. I should verify how the gateway is actually invoking these hooks.","thinkingSignature":"63ae160aec4bdaf619bba3ae5261d73c0256e5bb89c19aa4681f26bcf56c8936"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_6a307463355c4d7cab7da8a2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -r \"bootstrapFiles\\|agent:bootstrap\\|hook.*event\" ~/.openclaw/v8/src/ 2>/dev/null | grep -v \"node_modules\" | grep -v \".js.map\" | head -20"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_cbb861bc6dba4fc3be77370a","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -r \"type.*command\\|command.*type\\|session-summary\\|hoo