{"type":"message","id":"fe30503f","parentId":"f82c9d5b","timestamp":"2026-04-14T14:27:53.919Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_54e82d710985486da63c4c3c","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"config.js\ncontext\nexecutor\nindex.js\nobservability\npersistence\nrouter\nscheduler\nscoring\nsecurity\nskills\nutils"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":69,"aggregated":"config.js\ncontext\nexecutor\nindex.js\nobservability\npersistence\nrouter\nscheduler\nscoring\nsecurity\nskills\nutils","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776176873907}}
{"type":"message","id":"98900b2d","parentId":"fe30503f","timestamp":"2026-04-14T14:27:59.555Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"There's a `memory-bootstrap` skill with its own handler! Let me check that. That's likely the bootstrap hook I need.","thinkingSignature":"0b2c5d68e6673fd55118e7a5422267de20549fe0deced74c534b278ce3300634"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_115ccfa663f240cd82b12806","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/skills/memory-bootstrap/hooks/openclaw/handler.js 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":279,"output":70,"cacheRead":39616,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":39965,"cost":{"input":0.0000837,"output":0.000084,"cacheRead":0.0023769599999999996,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00254466}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776176873920,"responseId":"062d81e9d6f3464c1184796665295b25"}}
{"type":"message","id":"693af6b1","parentId":"98900b2d","timestamp":"2026-04-14T14:27:59.660Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_115ccfa663f240cd82b12806","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"/**\n * Memory Bootstrap Hook for OpenClaw\n *\n * Fires on agent:bootstrap event before workspace files are injected.\n * Injects MEMORY.md + recent session summaries as virtual bootstrap files.\n */\n\nconst handler = async (event) => {\n  // Safety checks for event structure\n  if (!event || typeof event !== 'object') return;\n  if (event.type !== 'agent' || event.action !== 'bootstrap') return;\n  if (!event.context || typeof event.context !== 'object') return;\n  if (!Array.isArray(event.context.bootstrapFiles)) return;\n\n  const workspaceDir = event.context.workspaceDir || process.env.OPENCLAW_WORKSPACE_DIR;\n  if (!workspaceDir) return;\n\n  const memoryRoot = `${workspaceDir}/memory`;\n  const memoryMdPath = `${workspaceDir}/MEMORY.md`;\n\n  // Read MEMORY.md (long-term memory index)\n  try {\n    const { readFile } = await import('node:fs/promises');\n    const memoryContent = await readFile(memoryMdPath, 'utf-8').catch(() => null);\n    if (memoryContent) {\n      event.context.bootstrapFiles.push({\n        path: 'MEMORY.md',\n        content: memoryContent.slice(0, 2000),\n        virtual: true,\n      });\n    }\n  } catch { /* skip */ }\n\n  // Read recent session summaries from memory/\n  try {\n    const { readdir, readFile } = await import('node:fs/promises');\n    const files = await readdir(memoryRoot);\n    const summaryFiles = files\n      .filter(f => (f.includes('summary') || f.match(/\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}/)) && f.endsWith('.md'))\n      .filter(f => !f.startsWith('MEMORY'))\n      .sort()\n      .reverse()\n      .slice(0, 3);\n\n    for (const file of summaryFiles) {\n      try {\n        const content = await readFile(`${memoryRoot}/${file}`, 'utf-8');\n        if (content.includes('<!-- summary-only -->') && content.length < 2000) {\n          event.context.bootstrapFiles.push({\n            path: `memory/${file}`,\n            content,\n            virtual: true,\n          });\n        } else if (!content.includes('<!-- summary-only -->')) {\n          event.context.bootstrapFiles.push({\n            path: `memory/${file}`,\n            content: content.slice(0, 1000),\n            virtual: true,\n          });\n        }\n      } catch { /* skip individual file errors */ }\n    }\n  } catch { /* skip directory errors */ }\n};\n\nexport default handler;\nmodule.exports = handler;\nmodule.exports.default = handler;"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":66,"aggregated":"/**\n * Memory Bootstrap Hook for OpenClaw\n *\n * Fires on agent:bootstrap event before workspace files are injected.\n * Injects MEMORY.md + recent session summaries as virtual bootstrap files.\n */\n\nconst handler = async (event) => {\n  // Safety checks for event structure\n  if (!event || typeof event !== 'object') return;\n  if (event.type !== 'agent' || event.action !== 'bootstrap') return;\n  if (!event.context || typeof event.context !== 'object') return;\n  if (!Array.isArray(event.context.bootstrapFiles)) return;\n\n  const workspaceDir = event.context.workspaceDir || process.env.OPENCLAW_WORKSPACE_DIR;\n  if (!workspaceDir) return;\n\n  const memoryRoot = `${workspaceDir}/memory`;\n  const memoryMdPath = `${workspaceDir}/MEMORY.md`;\n\n  // Read MEMORY.md (long-term memory index)\n  try {\n    const { readFile } = await import('node:fs/promises');\n    const memoryContent = await readFile(memoryMdPath, 'utf-8').catch(() => null);\n    if (memoryContent) {\n      event.context.bootstrapFiles.push({\n        path: 'MEMORY.md',\n        content: memoryContent.slice(0, 2000),\n        virtual: true,\n      });\n    }\n  } catch { /* skip */ }\n\n  // Read recent session summaries from memory/\n  try {\n    const { readdir, readFile } = await import('node:fs/promises');\n    const files = await readdir(memoryRoot);\n    const summaryFiles = files\n      .filter(f => (f.includes('summary') || f.match(/\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}/)) && f.endsWith('.md'))\n      .filter(f => !f.startsWith('MEMORY'))\n      .sort()\n      .reverse()\n      .slice(0, 3);\n\n    for (const file of summaryFiles) {\n      try {\n        const content = await readFile(`${memoryRoot}/${file}`, 'utf-8');\n        if (content.includes('<!-- summary-only -->') && content.length < 2000) {\n          event.context.bootstrapFiles.push({\n            path: `memory/${file}`,\n            content,\n            virtual: true,\n          });\n        } else if (!content.includes('<!-- summary-only -->')) {\n          event.context.bootstrapFiles.push({\n            path: `memory/${file}`,\n            content: content.slice(0, 1000),\n            virtual: true,\n          });\n        }\n      } catch { /* skip individual file errors */ }\n    }\n  } catch { /* skip directory errors */ }\n};\n\nexport default handler;\nmodule.exports = handler;\nmodule.exports.default = handler;","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776176879647}}
{"type":"message","id":"994827a2","parentId":"693af6b1","timestamp":"2026-04-14T14:28:13.003Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have the full picture. There are TWO bootstrap hooks:\n\n1. `hooks/handler.js` (and `handler.ts`) - Self-Improvement + Session-Summary bootstrap hook\n   - Fires on `agent:bootstrap`\n   - Injects previous session summary from memory/*.md\n   - Uses `event.context.bootstrapFiles.push()`\n   - This is a HOOK in the hooks/ directory\n\n2. `skills/memory-bootstrap/hooks/openclaw/handler.js` - Memory Bootstrap skill hook\n   - Also fires on `agent:bootstrap`\n   - Injects MEMORY.md + recent session summaries\n   - Also uses `event.context.bootstrapFiles.push()`\n   - This is a SKILL in the skills/ directory\n\nSo the session-summary hook writes a file to `memory/` directory during the `command new/reset` event, then the bootstrap hook reads it back when the NEW session starts.\n\nThe issue is: the session-summary hook fires on `command new` event (from `commands.log`), but bootstrap fires on `agent:bootstrap`. The new session's first message (this conversation) should trigger the bootstrap.\n\nBut for this to work:\n1. Previous session ends with `/new` → `session-summary` hook fires → writes summary to `memory/`\n2. New session starts → `agent:bootstrap` fires → `handler.js` reads latest summary from `memory/` → injects it\n\nThe question is: does the session-summary hook actually fire when `/new` is triggered from the control UI? And does the bootstrap hook actually fire when the new session starts?\n\nLet me check if the session-summary hook is actually being triggered. The commands.log shows the `/new` events are being logged. The session-summary hook listens for `type === \"command\" && action === \"new\"`.\n\nBut wait - I need to understand how hooks are registered. \n\nThe hooks are registered in `openclaw.json` under `hooks.internal.entries`. I need to check how these hooks are actually invoked to see if they're wired up correctly.","thinkingSignature":"78f059674dba3a0305b92d58170afe8f008a4e0c38607ce64a6268bdc55fa2ee"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_fe66211577ce48e49ba58a9f","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -r \"internal.*hook\\|hook.*internal\\|entries.*session-summary\\|session-summary.*enabled\" ~/.openclaw/ --include=\"*.js\" -l 2>/dev/null | grep -v \"node_modules\" | head -10"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_f89c8a8dad3c4f9d89b07d7d","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -r \"session-summary\\|bootstrapFiles\\|agent:bootstrap\" ~/.openclaw/v8/src/ 2>/dev/null | grep -v \"node_modules\" | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":637,"output":548,"cacheRead":39872,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":41057,"cost":{"input":0.00019109999999999998,"output":0.0006575999999999999,"cacheRead":0.00239232,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00324102}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776176879662,"responseId":"062d81ef1ddfbaca5a6b743293ed2dac"}}
