{"type":"message","id":"4eb1933a","parentId":"2adbe893","timestamp":"2026-04-14T14:29:10.592Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the discrepancy now. The auto-score-classify hook writes ephemeral data to `EPHEMERAL_DIR` which is defined in the handler - let me find it.\n\nBut more importantly, I found a KEY issue:\n\nThe `session-summary` hook checks for `event.type === \"command\" && (event.action === \"new\" || event.action === \"reset\")`. \n\nBut the `handler.js` (bootstrap hook) checks for `event.type !== 'agent' || event.action !== 'bootstrap'`.\n\nThese are TWO DIFFERENT events! The session-summary hook is listening for `command new/reset` while the bootstrap hook is listening for `agent bootstrap`. \n\n\nNow I need to track down where these event types are actually emitted. The session-summary hook expects a command event with action new/reset, while the bootstrap hook expects an agent event with action bootstrap, so I need to find the code that dispatches these events and understand how the hook system is actually triggering them.","thinkingSignature":"44719f3e3ba2d7111d9023d2b4118c7089e8f38425894952e65b8cfde1fa4c19"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00e1a7ba637248fb866c878a","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -rn \"type.*command\\|command.*type\\|event\\.type\\|emit.*agent\\|emit.*command\" ~/.openclaw/ --include=\"*.js\" --include=\"*.ts\" 2>/dev/null | grep -v \"node_modules\" | grep -v \".map\" | grep -v \"handler.js\" | grep -v \"handler.ts\" | grep -v \"proxy/index\" | grep -v \"context-api\" | head -30"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_d29b8d65711546678cf265e9","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/hooks/auto-score-classify/handler.js 2>/dev/null | head -120"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":588,"output":359,"cacheRead":44224,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":45171,"cost":{"input":0.0001764,"output":0.00043079999999999995,"cacheRead":0