{"type":"message","id":"5e25a824","parentId":"20495029","timestamp":"2026-04-14T14:35:33.041Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see the full bootstrap flow in pi-embedded. The key is `resolveBootstrapContextForRun` which is called in the agent run path. Let me look at the bootstrap-budget.ts to understand the hook flow:\n\n```javascript\nasync function resolveBootstrapFilesForRun(params) {\n    ...\n    return sanitizeBootstrapFiles(filterHeartbeatBootstrapFile(await applyBootstrapHookOverrides({\n        files: applyContextModeFilter({...}),\n        ...\n    }), excludeHeartbeatBootstrapFile), params.warn);\n}\n```\n\nAnd `applyBootstrapHookOverrides`:\n```javascript\nasync function applyBootstrapHookOverrides(params) {\n    const event = createInternalHookEvent(\"agent\", \"bootstrap\", sessionKey, {\n        workspaceDir: params.workspaceDir,\n        bootstrapFiles: params.files,\n        cfg: params.config,\n        sessionKey: params.sessionKey,\n        sessionId: params.sessionId,\n        agentId\n    });\n    await triggerInternalHook(event);  // <-- fires all \"agent:bootstrap\" handlers\n    const updated = event.context.bootstrapFiles;\n    return Array.isArray(updated) ? updated : params.files;\n}\n```\n\nSo the hook fires, updates `event.context.bootstrapFiles`, and the updated array is returned. This all happens inside `resolveBootstrapFilesForRun`, which is called by `resolveBootstrapContextForRun`.\n\nNow the question is: does the `memory-bootstrap` skill hook get loaded? Let me check the openclaw.json for hook entries configuration. From the output above, `context_hook` is listed in `entries` with `enabled: true`. But this is a legacy config, not a directory-based hook.\n\n\nLooking at the internal hooks configuration, I see `session-memory`, `command-logger`, `self-improvement`, `context_hook`, `auto-score-classify`, and `session-summary` are all registered. The `context_hook` is likely the legacy handler that needs to be examined to understand how it relates to the memory-bootstrap skill.","thinkingSignature":"82ecd0532847f393851aadd9baf6571da4c369b8c8c0de18b21663393df5d3a0"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_976e61a3c0034833a78d054a","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json 2>/dev/null | python3 -m json.tool 2>/dev/null | grep -A 100 '\"hooks\"' | head -120"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1434,"output":459,"cacheRead":43712,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":45605,"cost":{"input":0.0004302,"output":0.0005507999999999999,"cacheRead":0.00262272,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0036037199999999995}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776177322352,"responseId":"062d83a9badb51eb2e8d18ff7d1e194f"}}
