                   },\n                    \"dbPath\": \"~/.openclaw/memory/lancedb\",\n                    \"autoCapture\": true,\n                    \"autoRecall\": true\n                }\n            },\n            \"memory-core\": {\n                \"enabled\": true,\n                \"config\": {\n                    \"dreaming\": {\n                        \"enabled\": true\n                    }\n                }\n            },\n            \"openclaw-weixin\": {\n                \"enabled\": true\n            },\n            \"volcengine\": {\n                \"enabled\": true\n            },\n            \"deepseek\": {","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776177333118}}
{"type":"message","id":"d33398c2","parentId":"2e665324","timestamp":"2026-04-14T14:35:46.579Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see that internal hooks are enabled via `\"hooks\": { \"internal\": { \"enabled\": true, \"entries\": { ... } } }`. The 6 entries are listed.But in server.impl, the config is accessed via `config?.hooks?.internal?.handlers` (legacy) or via loadWorkspaceHookEntries + shouldIncludeHook. So the new way uses a directory-based discovery.Let me check if there's a `hooks.internal.entries` that maps to the HOOK.md mechanism vs the old handlers mechanism.Actually wait - looking at the config section again:```json\"hooks\": {    \"internal\": {        \"enabled\": true,        \"entries\": {            \"session-memory\": { \"enabled\": true },            \"command-logger\": { \"enabled\": true },            \"self-improvement\": { \"enabled\": true },            \"context_hook\": { \"enabled\": true },            \"auto-score-classify\": { \"enabled\": true },            \"session-summary\": { \"enabled\": true }        }    }}```This has `entries` but the legacy code checks `handlers`. These might be two different configs! The old `handlers` config is:```json\"internal\": {    \"enabled\": true,    \"handlers\": [ ... old format ... ]}```But the current config has `entries` instead of `handlers`. Maybe the old handlers format is no longer being used, and the new `entries` format doesn't actually trigger the old handler loading mechanism!\n\nActually, looking at the server.impl code more carefully:\n\n```js// NEW directory-based hook loading\nconst eligible = loadWorkspaceHookEntries(workspaceDir, {    config: cfg,    managedHooksDir: opts?.managedHooksDir,    bundledHooksDir: opts?.bundledHooksDir}).filter((entry) => shouldIncludeHook({ entry, config: cfg }));// OLD legacy handler loading\nconst handlers = getLegacyInternalHookHandlers(cfg); // reads config?.hooks?.internal?.handlers\n\n\n```\n\nBoth paths run in loadInternalHooks. The shouldIncludeHook filter likely checks `entry.hook.name` against the `entries` config to determine which hooks to load. So the `entries` config drives the new directory-based loading mechanism, while the old `handlers` array is a fallback for legacy configurations.\n\nThe session-summary hook is registered in workspace at `~/.openclaw/hooks/session-summary/` with an HOOK.md file, which should be discovered by loadWorkspaceHookEntries. But the hook may not be firing at all—either it's not being discovered, or the event filtering is preventing it from running.\n\nLooking at session-updates, the session_start and session_end hooks are triggered through the hookRunner, and these might be what I need instead of or in addition to the session-summary hook.\n\n```","thinkingSignature":"ba0e1ed0859126ccb7777bc1b93d0c707e7a28e02e6897ca0d85c13777e34437"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_af78e13167424a2ba291ec91","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"buildSessionStartHookPayload\\|session_start\\|session_end\" ~/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/session-hooks-TpmBubJz.js 2>/dev/null | head -30"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_0ba67a7ac6a04ab98176905c","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/session-hooks-TpmBubJz.js 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":738,"output":697,"cacheRead":45120,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":46555,"cost":{"input":0.0002214,"output":0.0008364,"cacheRead":0.0027072,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.003765}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776177333122,"responseId":"062d83b5ce88fd8ec654c3ebba55620f"}}
