{"type":"message","id":"4f3c3e78","parentId":"79599439","timestamp":"2026-04-14T14:37:01.963Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting! The `session-summary` HOOK.md says:\n\n```json\n\"events\": [\"command:new\", \"command:reset\"]\n```\n\nSo it fires on `command:new` and `command:reset`. But `session-summary` hook in the config is listed under `hooks.internal.entries` with just `\"enabled\": true`. \n\nNow let me check the `context_hook` entry - it's also listed in `hooks.internal.entries` with just `\"enabled\": true`. This is a workspace hook. Let me check its files.\n\nWait, looking at the config, `context_hook` is listed under `hooks.internal.entries` as `{\"enabled\": true}` without a `module` or `handler` path. \n\nThat's odd - if it doesn't have a `module` property, how does OpenClaw know where to load it? Maybe workspace hooks discovered from the hooks directory get their config populated differently. Let me trace through the internal hooks configuration to understand how these workspace hooks are actually loaded and registered.","thinkingSignature":"03c35b885ee14addcff3db0d4ebb20ba0a871a2a06f8cbd21676ce16d9372979"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_905dd8546c8c4a88a8869f23","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/hooks/HOOK.md 2>/dev/null"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_be02dde55ef34e8db328deb6","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -la ~/.openclaw/hooks/ 2>/dev/null; ls -la ~/.openclaw/hooks/context-hook* 2>/dev/null; find ~/.openclaw/hooks -name \"context*\" 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":597,"output":309,"cacheRead":46976,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":47882,"cost":{"input":0.0001791,"output":0.00037079999999999996,"cacheRead":0.00281856,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0033684599999999998}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776177414362,"responseId":"062d84055c42f41dffc2ae58d9239151"}}
{"type":"message","id":"60e79d7b","parentId":"4f3c3e78","timestamp":"2026-04-14T14:37:02.050Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_905dd8546c8c4a88a8869f23","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: self-improvement\ndescription: \"Injects self-improvement reminder during agent bootstrap\"\nmetadata: {\"openclaw\":{\"emoji\":\"🧠\",\"events\":[\"agent:bootstrap\"]}}\n---\n\n# Self-Improvement Hook\n\nInjects a reminder to evaluate learnings during agent bootstrap.\n\n## What It Does\n\n- Fires on `agent:bootstrap` (before workspace files are injected)\n- Adds a reminder block to check `.learnings/` for relevant entries\n- Prompts the agent to log corrections, errors, and discoveries\n\n## Configuration\n\nNo configuration needed. Enable with:\n\n```bash\nopenclaw hooks enable self-improvement\n```"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":52,"aggregated":"---\nname: self-improvement\ndescription: \"Injects self-improvement reminder during agent bootstrap\"\nmetadata: {\"openclaw\":{\"emoji\":\"🧠\",\"events\":[\"agent:bootstrap\"]}}\n---\n\n# Self-Improvement Hook\n\nInjects a reminder to evaluate learnings during agent bootstrap.\n\n## What It Does\n\n- Fires on `agent:bootstrap` (before workspace files are injected)\n- Adds a reminder block to check `.learnings/` for relevant entries\n- Prompts the agent to log corrections, errors, and discoveries\n\n## Configuration\n\nNo configuration needed. Enable with:\n\n```bash\nopenclaw hooks enable self-improvement\n```","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776177422047}}
