{"type":"message","id":"33e2d10a","parentId":"a74e1b32","timestamp":"2026-04-14T14:37:08.689Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me look at the internal hooks registration and find what \"context_hook\" in openclaw.json maps to. The issue is that the HOOK.md file at `~/.openclaw/hooks/HOOK.md` only describes the \"self-improvement\" hook (with `agent:bootstrap`), but there's no handler.js for context_hook in the workspace hooks directory.\n\nLet me check the openclaw managed hooks.\n","thinkingSignature":"e294fea29eb049b6f42cc1578613adeda9e8e7746b2528ad55d0a6dd6d3e4404"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_c5d8f685fea94ddaac87ca45","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"find ~/.openclaw -name \"*.js\" -path \"*/hooks/*\" ! -path \"*/node_modules/*\" 2>/dev/null | head -20"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_ab140e476cb54fe5a334d5bf","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check what managed hooks exist\nfind ~/.openclaw -name \"HOOK.md\" 2>/dev/null | xargs -I{} dirname {} | sort -u | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":577,"output":197,"cacheRead":47552,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":48326,"cost":{"input":0.00017309999999999998,"output":0.0002364,"cacheRead":0.00285312,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00326262}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776177422055,"responseId":"062d840d9d59064dfa81ad9bc8005815"}}
