{"type":"message","id":"9a624397","parentId":"bade9964","timestamp":"2026-04-14T14:37:18.361Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So the hooks that are installed:\n1. `hooks/auto-score-classify/handler.js` - scores/classifies messages\n2. `hooks/session-summary/handler.js` - generates session summaries\n3. `hooks/context-hook.js` - some context hook\n4. `hooks/handler.js` - the bootstrap hook (handler.js)\n5. `skills/self-improving-agent/hooks/openclaw/handler.js` - self-improvement hook\n6. `skills/memory-bootstrap/hooks/openclaw/handler.js` - memory bootstrap hook\n\nThe `openclaw.json` has `context_hook` entry but the HOOK.md for it is in `hooks/` directory (not in a subdirectory). And `self-improvement` is also listed but its actual hook is in `skills/self-improving-agent/hooks/openclaw/`.\n\nWait - looking at the openclaw.json entries:\n- `context_hook` → `hooks/context-hook.js` (in the hooks/ root)\n- `self-improvement` → `skills/self-improving-agent/hooks/openclaw/handler.js`\n- `session-summary` → `hooks/session-summary/handler.js`\n- `auto-score-classify` → `hooks/auto-score-classify/handler.js`\n\n\nBut there's no `memory-bootstrap` entry in the openclaw.json config, even though the skill is installed at `skills/memory-bootstrap/hooks/openclaw/`. The bootstrap hook at `hooks/handler.js` might be the memory-bootstrap hook, or there's a mismatch between what's installed and what's configured.","thinkingSignature":"b67a4c568a30fff6454ff44df492e7f98778c98d6dc3ceefc543d2a7d569f5d3"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_74394cf97a334df1bd13ec0e","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/hooks/handler.js 2>/dev/null | head -50"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_12c96f16a2cd4fbca4cb07e9","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/hooks/context-hook.js 2>/dev/null | head -30"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":373,"output":393,"cacheRead":48064,"cacheWrite":0,