{"type":"message","id":"b0e64a75","parentId":"9a624397","timestamp":"2026-04-14T14:37:18.445Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_74394cf97a334df1bd13ec0e","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"/**\n * Self-Improvement + Session-Summary Bootstrap Hook for OpenClaw\n *\n * Injects:\n * 1. Self-Improvement reminder during agent bootstrap\n * 2. Previous session's summary (memory/*-session-summary.md) as bootstrap context\n *\n * Fires on agent:bootstrap event before workspace files are injected.\n */\n\nimport fs from 'node:fs';\nimport path from 'node:path';\nimport os from 'node:os';\n\nconst SELF_IMPROVEMENT_REMINDER = `## Self-Improvement Reminder\n\nAfter completing tasks, evaluate if any learnings should be captured:\n\n**Log when:**\n- User corrects you → \\`.learnings/LEARNINGS.md\\`\n- Command/operation fails → \\`.learnings/ERRORS.md\\`\n- User wants missing capability → \\`.learnings/FEATURE_REQUESTS.md\\`\n- You discover your knowledge was wrong → \\`.learnings/LEARNINGS.md\\`\n- You find a better approach → \\`.learnings/LEARNINGS.md\\`\n\n**Promote when pattern is proven:**\n- Behavioral patterns → \\`SOUL.md\\`\n- Workflow improvements → \\`AGENTS.md\\`\n- Tool gotchas → \\`TOOLS.md\\`\n\nKeep entries simple: date, title, what happened, what to do differently.`;\n\n/**\n * Find and read the most recent session-summary file.\n * Looks in memory/ for *-session-summary.md files, returns most recent by mtime.\n */\nasync function getLatestSessionSummary() {\n  try {\n    const memoryDir = path.join(\n      process.env.OPENCLAW_WORKSPACE_DIR || path.join(os.homedir(), '.openclaw', 'workspace'),\n      'memory'\n    );\n\n    const files = await fs.promises.readdir(memoryDir);\n    const summaryFiles = files.filter(f => f.endsWith('-session-summary.md'));\n\n    if (summaryFiles.length === 0) return null;\n\n    // Sort by mtime descending\n    const withMtime = await Promise.all("}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":54,"aggregated":"/**\n * Self-Improvement + Session-Summary Bootstrap Hook for OpenClaw\n *\n * Injects:\n * 1. Self-Improvement reminder during agent bootstrap\n * 2. Previous session's summary (memory/*-session-summary.md) as bootstrap context\n *\n * Fires on agent:bootstrap event before workspace files are injected.\n */\n\nimport fs from 'node:fs';\nimport path from 'node:path';\nimport os from 'node:os';\n\nconst SELF_IMPROVEMENT_REMINDER = `## Self-Improvement Reminder\n\nAfter completing tasks, evaluate if any learnings should be captured:\n\n**Log when:**\n- User corrects you → \\`.learnings/LEARNINGS.md\\`\n- Command/operation fails → \\`.learnings/ERRORS.md\\`\n- User wants missing capability → \\`.learnings/FEATURE_REQUESTS.md\\`\n- You discover your knowledge was wrong → \\`.learnings/LEARNINGS.md\\`\n- You find a better approach → \\`.learnings/LEARNINGS.md\\`\n\n**Promote when pattern is proven:**\n- Behavioral patterns → \\`SOUL.md\\`\n- Workflow improvements → \\`AGENTS.md\\`\n- Tool gotchas → \\`TOOLS.md\\`\n\nKeep entries simple: date, title, what happened, what to do differently.`;\n\n/**\n * Find and read the most recent session-summary file.\n * Looks in memory/ for *-session-summary.md files, returns most recent by mtime.\n */\nasync function getLatestSessionSummary() {\n  try {\n    const memoryDir = path.join(\n      process.env.OPENCLAW_WORKSPACE_DIR || path.join(os.homedir(), '.openclaw', 'workspace'),\n      'memory'\n    );\n\n    const files = await fs.promises.readdir(memoryDir);\n    const summaryFiles = files.filter(f => f.endsWith('-session-summary.md'));\n\n    if (summaryFiles.length === 0) return null;\n\n    // Sort by mtime descending\n    const withMtime = await Promise.all(","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776177438442}}
{"type":"message","id":"655091ea","parentId":"b0e64a75","timestamp":"2026-04-14T14:37:18.449Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_12c96f16a2cd4fbca4cb07e9","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"/**\n * Context Hook for OpenClaw\n * \n * 监听消息事件，自动调用保护层context模块\n * \n * 支持的事件:\n * - message:receive: 用户发送消息\n * - message:send: AI 发送消息\n * - agent:response: Agent 回复\n */\n\nconst handler = async (event) => {\n  try {\n    // 检查是否有全局上下文接口\n    if (!global.openclaw || !global.openclaw.addContextMessage) {\n      // 尝试加载保护层\n      try {\n        const protection = await import(process.env.HOME + '/.openclaw/protection/index.js');\n        await protection.default.init();\n      } catch (e) {\n        console.log('[ContextHook] 保护层未加载，跳过');\n        return;\n      }\n    }\n\n    // 处理用户消息\n    if (event.type === 'message' || event.type === 'message:receive') {\n      const content = event.message?.content || event.content || '';\n      if (content) {\n        global.openclaw?.addContextMessage('user', content, event.taskId);"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":58,"aggregated":"/**\n * Context Hook for OpenClaw\n * \n * 监听消息事件，自动调用保护层context模块\n * \n * 支持的事件:\n * - message:receive: 用户发送消息\n * - message:send: AI 发送消息\n * - agent:response: Agent 回复\n */\n\nconst handler = async (event) => {\n  try {\n    // 检查是否有全局上下文接口\n    if (!global.openclaw || !global.openclaw.addContextMessage) {\n      // 尝试加载保护层\n      try {\n        const protection = await import(process.env.HOME + '/.openclaw/protection/index.js');\n        await protection.default.init();\n      } catch (e) {\n        console.log('[ContextHook] 保护层未加载，跳过');\n        return;\n      }\n    }\n\n    // 处理用户消息\n    if (event.type === 'message' || event.type === 'message:receive') {\n      const content = event.message?.content || event.content || '';\n      if (content) {\n        global.openclaw?.addContextMessage('user', content, event.taskId);","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776177438446}}
{"type":"message","id":"388c9eaa","parentId":"655091ea","timestamp":"2026-04-14T14:37:29.505Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see the actual handlers! There are TWO different handlers:\n\n1. `~/.openclaw/hooks/handler.js` - This is the \"Self-Improvement + Session-Summary Bootstrap Hook\" that fires on `agent:bootstrap`. It reads session summaries from `memory/` directory.\n\n2. `~/.openclaw/hooks/context-hook.js` - This is the \"Context Hook\" that listens to message events.\n\nBut wait - the HOOK.md in `~/.openclaw/hooks/` only describes `self-improvement`. The `handler.js` has BOTH self-improvement AND session-summary bootstrap reading logic combined in the same file!\n \nLooking at the file structure, `self-improvement.js` is empty (0 bytes), but `handler.js` contains the actual self-improvement logic AND session-summary reading combined. So the HOOK.md documents only self-improvement, yet the actual handler.js file is doing double duty handling both functionalities. I see there are two separate hook systems at play here. The internal hooks registered in openclaw.json include session-summary, which should be firing on `command:new` and `command:reset` events based on its HOOK.md configuration. But I'm also seeing workspace-based hooks through the skills directory, particularly memory-bootstrap and self-improving-agent, which fire on `agent:bootstrap` events and inject bootstrap files. The fact that bootstrap files aren't being injected suggests these hooks aren't being loaded properly, so I need to trace through the hook loading logic to understand why the workspace hooks aren't being registered alongside the internal ones. The bootstrap hook is registered in openclaw.json and should fire during agent startup, but the summary wasn't injected this time. I'm wondering if the session summary file simply doesn't exist yet for today, or if the hook ran before the summary was created. Let me check what files are actually in the memory directory and when they were last modified.","thinkingSignature":"46a0f317980491d1aeb983a2c08cd82dff402e56ffdb374db70310a1db6ad67a"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_bba2a655aa704392bf613c8c","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -la ~/.openclaw/workspace/main/memory/*session-summary* 2>/dev/null; ls -la ~/.openclaw/workspace/main/memory/ 2>/dev/null | tail -20"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_9683df8bcd7c4007aeb72b9c","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/hooks/handler.js 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":794,"output":477,"cacheRead":48384,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":49655,"cost":{"input":0.0002382,"output":0.0005723999999999999,"cacheRead":0.0029030399999999995,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0037136399999999994}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776177438451,"responseId":"062d841e7291dbfd35a1ca2faf84d8b6"}}
