{"type":"message","id":"1ebcc042","parentId":"3b5687e0","timestamp":"2026-04-14T14:39:04.305Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the hook discovery order:```jsreturn [\n  ...extraHooks,\n  ...bundledHooks,\n  ...pluginHooks,\n  ...managedHooks,\n  ...workspaceHooks\n];\n```The `managedHooksDir` is `~/.openclaw/hooks` (from `CONFIG_DIR`). The `workspaceHooksDir` is `~/.openclaw/workspace/main/hooks`.\n\nSo managed hooks (from `~/.openclaw/hooks/`) come BEFORE workspace hooks (from `~/.openclaw/workspace/main/hooks/`).\n\nSince we have `~/.openclaw/hooks/handler.js` (self-improvement + session-summary bootstrap) and `~/.openclaw/hooks/session-summary/handler.js` (the full session-summary hook that fires on `command:new/reset`), the question is: are these being discovered correctly?\n\nLet me check if there's a `hooks` subdirectory in `~/.openclaw/workspace/main/`:","thinkingSignature":"d2593e793b87b3f8e6a6c3ff4cd700fcf8dc1f16167db96c0a867ae9936f4671"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_bf9e73b128124d89abb67935","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -la ~/.openclaw/workspace/main/hooks/ 2>/dev/null || echo \"no workspace/main/hooks dir\""}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_ca68e0530b7a468bb3c56080","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check if there's a bundled hooks dir in the openclaw dist\nls ~/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/hooks/bundled/ 2>/dev/null | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1069,"output":304,"cacheRead":57536,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":58909,"cost":{"input":0.0003207,"output":0.0003648,"cacheRead":0.0034521599999999997,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00413766}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776177536951,"responseId":"062d8481a921b821d5e1e33273b4dd2b"}}
