{"type":"message","id":"a3332f7e","parentId":"89cb9e32","timestamp":"2026-04-14T14:39:37.709Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so the ephemeral directory has proper permissions (755 for dir, 600 for files). And sessions.json is also owned by ai with 600 permissions. Gateway runs as ai, so it should be able to write there.\n\nThe ephemeral directory only has 2 entries (agent:fast_agent:main and agent:main:main) - but those are from Apr 13. The ephemeral directory was created on Apr 14 22:23 (same time as current session start). So the ephemeral wasn't written by this session yet - but that's expected, ephemeral writes per-message, not on session start.\n\nWait - but this session started at 22:23, and the session-summary hook should have run (since the HOOK.md events include command:new/reset). But no session-summary was created in memory/...\n\nActually wait - I realize something. The session-summary hook is in `~/.openclaw/hooks/session-summary/`. But the `handler.js` is 23KB, which is the full session-summary handler. And it's in the `~/.openclaw/hooks/` directory, which is the \"managed hooks dir\" (from `~/.openclaw/hooks/`).\n\nBut the hook discovery also looks at `~/.openclaw/workspace/main/hooks/` for workspace hooks, and that directory doesn't exist.\n\nThe key question is: does the gateway load hooks from `~/.openclaw/hooks/`? From the discovery code:\n- `managedHooksDir = ~/.openclaw/hooks/` \n- `workspaceHooksDir = ~/.openclaw/workspace/main/hooks/` (doesn't exist)\n- `bundledHooksDir` = openclaw dist bundled dir (empty)\n\n\n- `pluginHookDirs` = plugin-provided hook dirs\n\nSo `~/.openclaw/hooks/` (managed) SHOULD be loaded. And `session-summary` IS in the openclaw.json enabled list.\n\nSo the question is WHY ISN'T IT WORKING?\n\nI need to check the `resolveHookEntries` function to see if there's something wrong with how the session-summary hook is being registered or resolved. Let me look at the actual hook event emission to understand what's happening.\n\nThe gateway uses internal hooks (event type/action pairs like \"command:new\") that are triggered via `triggerInternalHook` and registered through `registerInternalHook`. These are separate from plugin hooks. The session-summary hook in `~/.openclaw/hooks/session-summary/` is registered as an internal hook in `openclaw.json`, so it should be getting triggered when command:new events fire. The hook code shows it's checking for `event.type === \"command\" && (event.action === \"new\" || event.action === \"reset\")` and calling `resolveSessionFile(event.context || {}, workspaceDir)`, so I need to trace why that's not working as expected.\n\nLet me check the hook event configuration itself - the HOOK.md declares events as `[\"command:new\", \"command:reset\"]`, which should match the internal hook system. But maybe the events aren't being emitted properly, or there's an issue with how the context is being passed to the hook handler.\n\nActually, I should trace through the gateway's internal hook system to see if it supports the \"command\" event type at all - the `triggerInternalHook` function calls `get(event.type, event.action)` to dispatch to registered handlers, so I need to verify what event types are actually registered and being triggered when `/new` executes.","thinkingSignature":"d386f6be45a0e1cd444583009fa8115e4d1d2840ac8eb7c3974cf812c0361d04"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_358c35669faf4d00bf10f3f3","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sed -n '100,170p' ~/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/internal-hooks-B5x-V_Su.js 2>/dev/null"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_83f460a695394f5eacb1a676","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check what events the internal hooks system knows about\ngrep -n \"command.*new\\|command.*reset\\|emit.*command\\|trigger.*command\" ~/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/internal-hooks-B5x-V_Su.js 2>/dev/null | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":756,"output":848,"cacheRead":58688,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":60292,"cost":{"input":0.00022679999999999998,"output":0.0010176,"cacheRead":0.00352128,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00476568}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776177560919,"responseId":"062d8499498632a77a76e34dea9485ec"}}
