{"type":"message","id":"6ecd2003","parentId":"ff43d6c1","timestamp":"2026-04-14T14:40:03.920Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_d623617451db4d33913271ec","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"precedence: 30,\n\t\ttrustedLocalCode: true,\n\t\tdefaultEnableMode: \"default-on\",\n\t\tcanOverride: [\n\t\t\t\"openclaw-bundled\",\n\t\t\t\"openclaw-managed\",\n\t\t\t\"openclaw-plugin\"\n\t\t],\n\t\tcanBeOverriddenBy: [\"openclaw-managed\"]\n\t},\n\t\"openclaw-workspace\": {\n\t\tprecedence: 40,\n\t\ttrustedLocalCode: true,\n\t\tdefaultEnableMode: \"explicit-opt-in\",\n\t\tcanOverride: [\"openclaw-workspace\"],\n\t\tcanBeOverriddenBy: [\"openclaw-workspace\"]\n\t}\n};\nfunction getHookSourcePolicy(source) {\n\treturn HOOK_SOURCE_POLICIES[source];\n}\nfunction resolveHookConfig(config, hookKey) {\n\tconst hooks = config?.hooks?.internal?.entries;\n\tif (!hooks || typeof hooks !== \"object\") return;\n\tconst entry = hooks[hookKey];\n\tif (!entry || typeof entry !== \"object\") return;\n\treturn entry;\n}\nfunction resolveHookEnableState(params) {\n\tconst { entry, config } = params;\n\tconst hookKey = resolveHookKey(entry.hook.name, entry);\n\tconst hookConfig = params.hookConfig ?? resolveHookConfig(config, hookKey);\n\tif (entry.hook.source === \"openclaw-plugin\") return { enabled: true };\n\tif (hookConfig?.enabled === false) return {\n\t\tenabled: false,\n\t\treason: \"disabled in config\"\n\t};\n\tif (getHookSourcePolicy(entry.hook.source).defaultEnableMode === \"explicit-opt-in\" && hookConfig?.enabled !== true) return {\n\t\tenabled: false,\n\t\treason: \"workspace hook (disabled by default)\"\n\t};"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":56,"aggregated":"precedence: 30,\n\t\ttrustedLocalCode: true,\n\t\tdefaultEnableMode: \"default-on\",\n\t\tcanOverride: [\n\t\t\t\"openclaw-bundled\",\n\t\t\t\"openclaw-managed\",\n\t\t\t\"openclaw-plugin\"\n\t\t],\n\t\tcanBeOverriddenBy: [\"openclaw-managed\"]\n\t},\n\t\"openclaw-workspace\": {\n\t\tprecedence: 40,\n\t\ttrustedLocalCode: true,\n\t\tdefaultEnableMode: \"explicit-opt-in\",\n\t\tcanOverride: [\"openclaw-workspace\"],\n\t\tcanBeOverriddenBy: [\"openclaw-workspace\"]\n\t}\n};\nfunction getHookSourcePolicy(source) {\n\treturn HOOK_SOURCE_POLICIES[source];\n}\nfunction resolveHookConfig(config, hookKey) {\n\tconst hooks = config?.hooks?.internal?.entries;\n\tif (!hooks || typeof hooks !== \"object\") return;\n\tconst entry = hooks[hookKey];\n\tif (!entry || typeof entry !== \"object\") return;\n\treturn entry;\n}\nfunction resolveHookEnableState(params) {\n\tconst { entry, config } = params;\n\tconst hookKey = resolveHookKey(entry.hook.name, entry);\n\tconst hookConfig = params.hookConfig ?? resolveHookConfig(config, hookKey);\n\tif (entry.hook.source === \"openclaw-plugin\") return { enabled: true };\n\tif (hookConfig?.enabled === false) return {\n\t\tenabled: false,\n\t\treason: \"disabled in config\"\n\t};\n\tif (getHookSourcePolicy(entry.hook.source).defaultEnableMode === \"explicit-opt-in\" && hookConfig?.enabled !== true) return {\n\t\tenabled: false,\n\t\treason: \"workspace hook (disabled by default)\"\n\t};","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776177603917}}
{"type":"message","id":"45bcadc5","parentId":"6ecd2003","timestamp":"2026-04-14T14:40:25.112Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see it clearly! The `session-summary` hook has source `\"openclaw-workspace\"`. According to the policy:\n\n```javascript\n\"openclaw-workspace\": {\n    precedence: 40,\n    trustedLocalCode: true,\n    defaultEnableMode: \"explicit-opt-in\",  // ← Requires explicit enable\n    canOverride: [\"openclaw-workspace\"],\n    canBeOverriddenBy: [\"openclaw-workspace\"]\n}\n```\n\nThe `defaultEnableMode: \"explicit-opt-in\"` means the hook is disabled by default unless explicitly enabled. And looking at `resolveHookEnableState`:\n\n```javascript\nif (getHookSourcePolicy(entry.hook.source).defaultEnableMode === \"explicit-opt-in\" && hookConfig?.enabled !== true) return {\n    enabled: false,\n    reason: \"workspace hook (disabled by default)\"\n};\n```\n\nNow let me check the config for `session-summary`:\n\n```json\n\"session-summary\": {\n    \"enabled\": true\n}\n```\n\nWait, the config shows `\"enabled\": true` for session-summary! So it should be enabled...\n\nBut wait - there's another check in `shouldIncludeHook`:\n\n```javascript\nif (!resolveHookEnableState({ entry, config, hookConfig }).enabled) return false;\nreturn evaluateHookRuntimeEligibility({...});\n```\n\nLet me check `resolveHookEnableState` more carefully:\n\n```javascript\nfunction resolveHookEnableState(params) {\n    const { entry, config } = params;\n    const hookKey = resolveHookKey(entry.hook.name, entry);\n    const hookConfig = params.hookConfig ?? resolveHookConfig(config, hookKey);\n    if (entry.hook.source === \"openclaw-plugin\") return { enabled: true };\n    if (hookConfig?.enabled === false) return { enabled: false, reason: \"disabled in config\" };\n    if (getHookSourcePolicy(entry.hook.source).defaultEnableMode === \"explicit-opt-in\" && hookConfig?.enabled !== true) return {\n        enabled: false,\n        reason: \"workspace hook (disabled by default)\"\n    };\n```\n\nSo even though the config has `enabled: true`, the `defaultEnableMode: \"explicit-opt-in\"` check is triggering because the hook isn't explicitly enabled in the config. The config entry for `session-summary` being `true` should override this, but something's not matching up. Let me trace through what `hookConfig?.enabled` actually resolves to when the config says `\"enabled\": true`. true` is truthy, so that check passes. But then the `defaultEnableMode === \"explicit-opt-in\"` condition triggers because `hookConfig?.enabled` is actually `true`, not `undefined`. This means the function returns `false` for a workspace hook that should be enabled.\n\nWait, I need to reconsider the logic here. The condition checks if `hookConfig?.enabled !== true`, and since `true !== true` is `false`, the whole expression short-circuits and returns early without checking `defaultEnableMode`. So workspace hooks should work correctly when `enabled: true` is set in the config. But then why would the session-summary hook not be firing?\n\nLet me check if there's a priority issue between the self-improvement hook from `~/.openclaw/hooks/handler.js` and the session-summary hook from the skills directory. The precedence values show `openclaw-managed` at 20 and `openclaw-workspace` at 40, so the workspace hook should take precedence. But maybe there's something else preventing it from executing properly.\n\nActually, looking more carefully at the config - the `openclaw.json` shows `\"self-improvement\": { \"enabled\": true }` but there's no explicit config entry for `session-summary` in `hooks.internal.entries`. The session-summary hook comes from `~/.openclaw/hooks/session-summary/handler.js` and is defined as `\"openclaw-workspace\"` source, which means it requires explicit opt-in since `defaultEnableMode: \"explicit-opt-in\"`. Without that explicit `enabled: true` in the config, it stays disabled.\n\nBut wait - the config I saw earlier actually did have `\"session-summary\": { \"enabled\": true }` listed. So the real problem must be something else. I need to trace through the config path itself: `hooks.internal.entries.session-summary.enabled`. The issue is that `resolveHookConfig` is probably looking for the wrong key path or the config structure isn't what I think it is.\n\nLet me check if the HOOK.md metadata is even being read correctly by the hook loader. The session-summary hook is in `~/.openclaw/hooks/session-summary/HOOK.md` which maps to `workspaceDir/hooks/session-summary`. I need to verify the hook is actually being discovered and loaded properly.","thinkingSignature":"7233445bb714b129ecf56c64d330d3855298076aa5f622d85981bd04e11b1bc6"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_bd12f970af7547db9c4aeb0f","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/hooks/session-summary/HOOK.md 2>/dev/null | head -30"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_c5a9061a262f44cb9bb97bfb","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check how hooks are resolved - the key used in config vs the name in HOOK.md\ngrep -n \"resolveHookKey\\|hookKey\\|hook.name\" ~/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/config-BAAmv8_d.js 2>/dev/null | head -30"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":813,"output":1104,"cacheRead":62400,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":64317,"cost":{"input":0.0002439,"output":0.0013248,"cacheRead":0.0037439999999999995,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.005312699999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776177603922,"responseId":"062d84c37a3d28663b80746d45639664"}}
{"type":"message","id":"761556a6","parentId":"45bcadc5","timestamp":"2026-04-14T14:40:25.206Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_bd12f970af7547db9c4aeb0f","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: session-summary\ndescription: \"session 结束时（/new 或 /reset）生成结构化摘要，写入 memory/，供下次 bootstrap 读取。依赖 context.previousSessionEntry.sessionFile 读取刚结束的 session 内容。\"\nmetadata:\n  {\n    \"openclaw\": {\n      \"emoji\": \"📝\",\n      \"events\": [\"command:new\", \"command:reset\"],\n      \"requires\": {\n        \"bins\": [\"node\"],\n        \"config\": [\"workspace.dir\"]\n      },\n      \"always\": true\n    }\n  }\n---\n\n# session-summary\n\n每次 `/new` 或 `/reset` 触发时，异步生成刚结束 session 的结构化摘要。\n\n## 行为\n\n- **异步执行**：hook 立即返回，摘要生成在后台，不阻塞命令响应\n- **降级策略**：LLM 不可用或生成失败时，写入规则摘要，不报错不中断\n- **文件格式**：`memory/YYYY-MM-DD-{slug}.md`，带 `<!-- summary-only -->` 标记\n\n## 摘要格式\n\n```markdown"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":54,"aggregated":"---\nname: session-summary\ndescription: \"session 结束时（/new 或 /reset）生成结构化摘要，写入 memory/，供下次 bootstrap 读取。依赖 context.previousSessionEntry.sessionFile 读取刚结束的 session 内容。\"\nmetadata:\n  {\n    \"openclaw\": {\n      \"emoji\": \"📝\",\n      \"events\": [\"command:new\", \"command:reset\"],\n      \"requires\": {\n        \"bins\": [\"node\"],\n        \"config\": [\"workspace.dir\"]\n      },\n      \"always\": true\n    }\n  }\n---\n\n# session-summary\n\n每次 `/new` 或 `/reset` 触发时，异步生成刚结束 session 的结构化摘要。\n\n## 行为\n\n- **异步执行**：hook 立即返回，摘要生成在后台，不阻塞命令响应\n- **降级策略**：LLM 不可用或生成失败时，写入规则摘要，不报错不中断\n- **文件格式**：`memory/YYYY-MM-DD-{slug}.md`，带 `<!-- summary-only -->` 标记\n\n## 摘要格式\n\n```markdown","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776177625203}}
