{"type":"message","id":"b65fb320","parentId":"9e7ba465","timestamp":"2026-04-14T14:41:06.427Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No session-summary files created today. No ephemeral files either.\n\nLet me check if the session-summary hook is actually being loaded. The openclaw gateway is the main process running. Let me see what hooks are actually registered.\n\nActually, looking at the whole chain again:\n\n1. The `handler.js` in `~/.openclaw/hooks/` is a workspace hook (source = \"openclaw-workspace\")\n2. Workspace hooks need `enabled: true` in config to be loaded (explicit-opt-in mode)\n3. The config has `\"session-summary\": { \"enabled\": true }` but the key used is `session-summary`\n4. The hook name from HOOK.md is `session-summary` → key = `session-summary` ✓\n\n\n5. The `always: true` flag in metadata might be bypassing the explicit-opt-in requirement, so I need to trace through evaluateHookRuntimeEligibility to see if that's what's happening.","thinkingSignature":"be97ff77ebe0bd27906a064d6682d102a471666109d0e082d23803ea74534764"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_c21d765925c744dcb0f6b49c","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sed -n '105,140p' ~/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/config-BAAmv8_d.js 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":307,"output":250,"cacheRead":64064,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":64621,"cost":{"input":0.0000921,"output":0.0003,"cacheRead":0.00384384,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00423594}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776177660092,"responseId":"062d84fca9cef087e6914f9a63dcc70a"}}
{"type":"message","id":"d4b4f640","parentId":"b65fb320","timestamp":"2026-04-14T14:41:06.509Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_c21d765925c744dcb0f6b49c","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"function evaluateHookRuntimeEligibility(params) {\n\tconst { entry, config, hookConfig, eligibility } = params;\n\tconst remote = eligibility?.remote;\n\treturn evaluateRuntimeEligibility({\n\t\tos: entry.metadata?.os,\n\t\tremotePlatforms: remote?.platforms,\n\t\talways: entry.metadata?.always,\n\t\trequires: entry.metadata?.requires,\n\t\thasRemoteBin: remote?.hasBin,\n\t\thasAnyRemoteBin: remote?.hasAnyBin,\n\t\thasBin: hasBinary,\n\t\thasEnv: (envName) => Boolean(process.env[envName] || hookConfig?.env?.[envName]),\n\t\tisConfigPathTruthy: (configPath) => isConfigPathTruthy(config, configPath)\n\t});\n}\nfunction shouldIncludeHook(params) {\n\tconst { entry, config, eligibility } = params;\n\tconst hookConfig = resolveHookConfig(config, params.entry.metadata?.hookKey ?? params.entry.hook.name);\n\tif (!resolveHookEnableState({\n\t\tentry,\n\t\tconfig,\n\t\thookConfig\n\t}).enabled) return false;\n\treturn evaluateHookRuntimeEligibility({\n\t\tentry,\n\t\tconfig,\n\t\thookConfig,\n\t\teligibility\n\t});\n}\n//#endregion\nexport { resolveHookEntries as a, resolveHookEnableState as i, shouldIncludeHook as n, resolveHookConfig as r, isConfigPathTruthy as t };"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":52,"aggregated":"function evaluateHookRuntimeEligibility(params) {\n\tconst { entry, config, hookConfig, eligibility } = params;\n\tconst remote = eligibility?.remote;\n\treturn evaluateRuntimeEligibility({\n\t\tos: entry.metadata?.os,\n\t\tremotePlatforms: remote?.platforms,\n\t\talways: entry.metadata?.always,\n\t\trequires: entry.metadata?.requires,\n\t\thasRemoteBin: remote?.hasBin,\n\t\thasAnyRemoteBin: remote?.hasAnyBin,\n\t\thasBin: hasBinary,\n\t\thasEnv: (envName) => Boolean(process.env[envName] || hookConfig?.env?.[envName]),\n\t\tisConfigPathTruthy: (configPath) => isConfigPathTruthy(config, configPath)\n\t});\n}\nfunction shouldIncludeHook(params) {\n\tconst { entry, config, eligibility } = params;\n\tconst hookConfig = resolveHookConfig(config, params.entry.metadata?.hookKey ?? params.entry.hook.name);\n\tif (!resolveHookEnableState({\n\t\tentry,\n\t\tconfig,\n\t\thookConfig\n\t}).enabled) return false;\n\treturn evaluateHookRuntimeEligibility({\n\t\tentry,\n\t\tconfig,\n\t\thookConfig,\n\t\teligibility\n\t});\n}\n//#endregion\nexport { resolveHookEntries as a, resolveHookEnableState as i, shouldIncludeHook as n, resolveHookConfig as r, isConfigPathTruthy as t };","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776177666506}}
{"type":"message","id":"558c043b","parentId":"d4b4f640","timestamp":"2026-04-14T14:41:16.701Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `always` field is checked in `evaluateRuntimeEligibility` - if `always: true`, the hook runs regardless of eligibility checks. Let me check what `evaluateRuntimeEligibility` does with the `always` field.\n\nActually, let me step back and think about this more carefully. The `always: true` in the hook metadata is checked by the hook system to determine whether a hook should run. But the actual mechanism depends on how `evaluateRuntimeEligibility` processes it.\n\nBut more importantly - let me verify whether the `session-summary` hook from `~/.openclaw/hooks/session-summary/` (which has `source: \"openclaw-managed\"`) is actually being loaded by the gateway at startup, and whether it's enabled in the config.\n\n\nI need to check if the managed hooks directory is actually being discovered - there's a `managedHooksDir` that's loaded from `~/.openclaw/hooks/` according to the discovery function, and the `session-summary` hook is present there, so the question is whether the config is actually enabling it.\n\nLooking at the config, the `\"session-summary\": { \"enabled\": true }` entry should map to the hook discovered from that directory, but I need to verify that the hook name in the config matches what's being loaded and that the `resolveHookEnableState` function is properly checking the `enabled` flag.","thinkingSignature":"cfa6b61604be3e64dcaa7d68e9bb6a55c2c9c55147ac5536235926f627fcf60b"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_bc4f000b23f34fd497546ce4","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sed -n '38,62p' ~/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/config-BAAmv8_d.js 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":411,"output":338,"cacheRead":64320,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":65069,"cost":{"input":0.0001233,"output":0.0004056,"cacheRea