{"type":"message","id":"1127e7a2","parentId":"146bac1d","timestamp":"2026-04-14T14:41:28.858Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK now I can see the full picture clearly. The session-summary hook IS being loaded - but it's a workspace hook with source \"openclaw-workspace\", which has `defaultEnableMode: \"explicit-opt-in\"`. For workspace hooks, they need `enabled: true` in the config to be enabled.\n\nThe config has:\n```json\n\"session-summary\": {\n    \"enabled\": true\n}\n```\n\nSo `hookConfig?.enabled !== true` check would be `true !== true` = `false`. So it should pass. Wait, but `hookConfig` is the resolved config entry which IS `{ enabled: true }`. So `hookConfig?.enabled !== true` is `true !== true` = `false`, which means the hook is NOT disabled by this check. Good.\n\nThen `evaluateHookRuntimeEligibility` is called. What could fail there?\n\nWait - there's also the `resolveHookEnableState` first check:\n```javascript\nif (hookConfig?.enabled === false) return { enabled: false, reason: \"disabled in config\" };\n```\n\nThis only returns false when `enabled === false`. Since it's `true`, it passes.\n\nSo it IS enabled. Why isn't it firing then?\n\nLet me look at the `evaluateRuntimeEligibility` function to understand what could fail.","thinkingSignature":"a9f4cc3b707a0a7d5f744534e7b503fb02791382f17adcd8bbfdf5a7780643d9"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_070f113c0e1e4e39a6ee5d52","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"evaluateRuntimeEligibility\" ~/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/config-BAAmv8_d.js 2>/dev/null | head -5"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_baa153a8f85a4ccd9f35ba0a","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"function evaluateRuntimeEligibility\" ~/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/config-BAAmv8_d.js 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":329,"output":385,"cacheRead":64704,"cacheWr