{"type":"message","id":"0326165b","parentId":"7a70eb8d","timestamp":"2026-04-14T14:42:07.082Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The gateway logs go to stdout which is a pipe (not a file). So no persistent gateway.log.\n\nLet me think about what I know for certain from the investigation and give the user a clear verdict.\n\nThe session-summary hook fires on `command:new` and `command:reset`. The `emitResetCommandHooks` function in `commands-reset-hooks-B7jYf1QC.js` creates the event and calls `triggerInternalHook`. This part looks correct.\n\nBut the session-summary hook is in `~/.openclaw/hooks/` which is the \"managed hooks\" directory (since CONFIG_DIR = ~/.openclaw). The issue is that the hook source is \"openclaw-managed\".\n \nFor \"openclaw-managed\" hooks, the default enable mode is \"default-on\", so if the config has `\"session-summary\": { \"enabled\": true }`, it should be enabled. Let me check the config to verify this is actually set up correctly.\n\nLooking at the config, both `session-summary` and `auto-score-classify` are explicitly enabled, which means they should be active. So the problem isn't a config issue. Let me trace through the actual hook loading mechanism to see where it's breaking down.\n\nThe `loadInternalHooks` function in the gateway uses `loadWorkspaceHookEntries` to find hooks in the workspace directory, then filters them through `shouldIncludeHook` with the user's config. The hook entries themselves come from HOOK.md files in the hook directories, and they get loaded via `loadHookEntriesFromDir`. I need to verify whether the hooks are actually being discovered and loaded properly, or if something's failing silently in that process. The grep command might be truncating output, so let me try searching more specifically. The real question is whether session-summary and auto-score-classify are in the managed hooks directory at all—they should be at `~/.openclaw/hooks/`, which is where `discoverWorkspaceHookEntries` looks for `openclaw-managed` hooks.\n\nSince `discoverWorkspaceHookEntries` includes hooks from the managed directory with source \"openclaw-managed\", and both hooks have `enabled: true` in the config, they should be getting loaded. But they're not appearing in the current session, which suggests something else is preventing them from being registered despite the config being correct.\n\nLet me test the gateway directly to see if the hooks are actually being registered, or if there's something about how webchat sessions handle the new/reset command flow that's different from other session types.","thinkingSignature":"f7067cdd50e2dc0625cbb25ad688456f9c9e877e52ad76936a5e935b8f180981"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_7fa8329d03564dd8a3bad041","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Try to verify if hooks are being loaded by the gateway\n# by checking if there's a debug endpoint or similar\ncurl -s -H \"Authorization: Bearer 0da4fe1cb845fc8386105026ee6b941b288a2a4264a16ced\" http://127.0.0.1:3102/v1/hooks/status 2>/dev/null || echo \"no such endpoint\"\n# Check if there's a way to see loaded hooks via openclaw CLI\nopenclaw hooks list 2>/dev/null || echo \"hooks list failed\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":787,"output":653,"cacheRead":66880,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":68320,"cost":{"input":0.0002361,"output":0.0007836,"cacheRead":0.0040127999999999995,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0050325}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776177711986,"responseId":"062d852f094e500cc4bd18674baabb54"}}
{"type":"message","id":"a7c1ea75","parentId":"0326165b","timestamp":"2026-04-14T14:42:07.173Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_7fa8329d03564dd8a3bad041","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"<!doctype html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n  <head>\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\" />\n    <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\" />\n    <title>OpenClaw Control</title>\n    <meta name=\"color-scheme\" content=\"dark light\" />\n    <link rel=\"icon\" type=\"image/svg+xml\" href=\"./favicon.svg\" />\n    <link rel=\"icon\" type=\"image/png\" sizes=\"32x32\" href=\"./favicon-32.png\" />\n    <link rel=\"apple-touch-icon\" sizes=\"180x180\" href=\"./apple-touch-icon.png\" />\n    <script>\n      (function () {\n        var THEMES = { claw: 1, knot: 1, dash: 1 };\n        var MODES = { system: 1, light: 1, dark: 1 };\n        var LEGACY = {\n          dark: \"claw:dark\",\n          light: \"claw:light\",\n          openknot: \"knot:dark\",\n          fieldmanual: \"dash:dark\",\n          clawdash: \"dash:light\",\n          system: \"claw:system\",\n        };\n        try {\n          var keys = Object.keys(localStorage);\n          var raw;\n          for (var i = 0; i < keys.length; i++) {\n            if (keys[i].indexOf(\"openclaw.control.settings.v1\") === 0) {\n              raw = localStorage.getItem(keys[i]);\n              if (raw) break;\n            }\n          }\n          if (!raw) return;\n          var s = JSON.parse(raw);\n          var t = s && s.theme;\n          var m = s && s.themeMode;\n          if (typeof t !== \"string\") t = \"\";\n          if (typeof m !== \"string\") m = \"\";\n          var legacy = LEGACY[t];\n          var theme = THEMES[t] ? t : legacy ? legacy.split(\":\")[0] : \"claw\";\n          var mode = MODES[m] ? m : legacy ? legacy.split(\":\")[1] : \"system\";\n          if (mode === \"system\") {\n            mode = window.matchMedia(\"(prefers-color-scheme: light)\").matches ? \"light\" : \"dark\";\n          }\n          var resolved =\n            theme === \"knot\"\n              ? mode === \"light\"\n                ? \"openknot-light\"\n                : \"openknot\"\n              : theme === \"dash\"\n                ? mode === \"light\"\n                  ? \"dash-light\"\n                  : \"dash\"\n                : mode === \"light\"\n                  ? \"light\"\n                  : \"dark\";\n          document.documentElement.setAttribute(\"data-theme\", resolved);\n          document.documentElement.setAttribute(\n            \"data-theme-mode\",\n            resolved.indexOf(\"light\") !== -1 ? \"light\" : \"dark\",\n          );\n        } catch (e) {}\n      })();\n    </script>\n    <script type=\"module\" crossorigin src=\"./assets/index-Dts6VHgr.js\"></script>\n    <link rel=\"modulepreload\" crossorigin href=\"./assets/i18n-BTxWaFnv.js\">\n    <link rel=\"modulepreload\" crossorigin href=\"./assets/directive-Dk4hInuL.js\">\n    <link rel=\"modulepreload\" crossorigin href=\"./assets/format-1xo3usjI.js\">\n    <link rel=\"modulepreload\" crossorigin href=\"./assets/string-coerce-BcFtIWA_.js\">\n    <link rel=\"stylesheet\" crossorigin href=\"./assets/index-BVXsoScG.css\">\n  </head>\n  <body>\n    <openclaw-app></openclaw-app>\n  </body>\n</html>\nhooks list failed"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":58,"aggregated":"<!doctype html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n  <head>\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\" />\n    <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\" />\n    <title>OpenClaw Control</title>\n    <meta name=\"color-scheme\" content=\"dark light\" />\n    <link rel=\"icon\" type=\"image/svg+xml\" href=\"./favicon.svg\" />\n    <link rel=\"icon\" type=\"image/png\" sizes=\"32x32\" href=\"./favicon-32.png\" />\n    <link rel=\"apple-touch-icon\" sizes=\"180x180\" href=\"./apple-touch-icon.png\" />\n    <script>\n      (function () {\n        var THEMES = { claw: 1, knot: 1, dash: 1 };\n        var MODES = { system: 1, light: 1, dark: 1 };\n        var LEGACY = {\n          dark: \"claw:dark\",\n          light: \"claw:light\",\n          openknot: \"knot:dark\",\n          fieldmanual: \"dash:dark\",\n          clawdash: \"dash:light\",\n          system: \"claw:system\",\n        };\n        try {\n          var keys = Object.keys(localStorage);\n          var raw;\n          for (var i = 0; i < keys.length; i++) {\n            if (keys[i].indexOf(\"openclaw.control.settings.v1\") === 0) {\n              raw = localStorage.getItem(keys[i]);\n              if (raw) break;\n            }\n          }\n          if (!raw) return;\n          var s = JSON.parse(raw);\n          var t = s && s.theme;\n          var m = s && s.themeMode;\n          if (typeof t !== \"string\") t = \"\";\n          if (typeof m !== \"string\") m = \"\";\n          var legacy = LEGACY[t];\n          var theme = THEMES[t] ? t : legacy ? legacy.split(\":\")[0] : \"claw\";\n          var mode = MODES[m] ? m : legacy ? legacy.split(\":\")[1] : \"system\";\n          if (mode === \"system\") {\n            mode = window.matchMedia(\"(prefers-color-scheme: light)\").matches ? \"light\" : \"dark\";\n          }\n          var resolved =\n            theme === \"knot\"\n              ? mode === \"light\"\n                ? \"openknot-light\"\n                : \"openknot\"\n              : theme === \"dash\"\n                ? mode === \"light\"\n                  ? \"dash-light\"\n                  : \"dash\"\n                : mode === \"light\"\n                  ? \"light\"\n                  : \"dark\";\n          document.documentElement.setAttribute(\"data-theme\", resolved);\n          document.documentElement.setAttribute(\n            \"data-theme-mode\",\n            resolved.indexOf(\"light\") !== -1 ? \"light\" : \"dark\",\n          );\n        } catch (e) {}\n      })();\n    </script>\n    <script type=\"module\" crossorigin src=\"./assets/index-Dts6