{"type":"message","id":"41504f4a","parentId":"5c591490","timestamp":"2026-04-14T14:43:42.834Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me do one final check - let me see if the session-summary hook is correctly triggered. Looking at the code:\n\n1. `emitResetCommandHooks` creates event with `createInternalHookEvent(\"command\", params.action, params.sessionKey ?? \"\", {...})`\n2. This fires `triggerInternalHook(\"command\", \"new\")` which calls all handlers registered for `command` and `command:new`\n3. The session-summary handler checks `event.type === \"command\" && (event.action === \"new\" || event.action === \"reset\")`\n\nSo the event matching should work.\n\nThe issue might be that the handler is not being registered at all. Let me try to check if the gateway has actually registered the hook by looking at the process more carefully.\n\nActually wait - I should check if there's a `package.json` or module type issue. The handler.js uses ESM (`import` statements), and the gateway might be loading it differently.\n\nActually, looking at the code in `loadHookFromDir`:\n```js\nconst handlerCandidates = [\n  \"handler.ts\",\n  \"handler.js\",\n  \"index.ts\",\n  \"index.js\"\n];\n```\n\nIt checks for handler files. Then:\n```js\nconst safeCandidatePath = resolveBoundaryFilePath({\n  absolutePath: path.join(params.hookDir, candidate),\n  rootPath: params.hookDir,\n  boundaryLabel: \"hook directory\"\n});\n```\n\nIf the file passes boundary checks, it's used as `handlerPath`.\n\nThen the hook entry has:\n```js\nreturn {\n  hook: {\n    name,\n    description,\n    source: params.source,\n    pluginId: params.pluginId,\n    filePath: hookMdPath,\n    baseDir,\n    handlerPath\n  },\n  frontmatter\n};\n```\n\nAnd later in `loadInternalHooks`:\n```js\nconst mod = await import(buildImportUrl(safeHandlerPath, entry.hook.source));\n```\n\nThis imports the handler. The `buildImportUrl` adds a query parameter or something to force the correct module type. Let me check what `buildImportUrl` does.\n\nActually, I think the key issue might be something simpler. \n\nI should check whether the `always` flag in the hook metadata is actually being evaluated properly. The `evaluateRuntimeEligibility` function does check for `always === true`, but maybe it's not being read correctly from the frontmatter metadata.\n\nLet me trace through how the frontmatter metadata gets parsed and stored in the hook entry, then passed to the eligibility evaluation function. The `resolveHookInvocationPolicy` function extracts the metadata from frontmatter, so I need to verify that's working correctly.","thinkingSignature":"6135b8b8949836cc441994e24398c357894d2c48cd97366732e9c5d90378a1f0"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_efef8f7cd87d409aa76c1f59","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"resolveHookInvocationPolicy\\|always\\|invocation\" ~/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/frontmatter-B7RzFZO5.js 2>/dev/null | head -30"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_19e775bd3124428e98f64466","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"invocation\\|always\" ~/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/frontmatter-B7RzFZO5.js 2>/dev/null | head -30"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":199,"output":677,"cacheRead":71616,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":72492,"cost":{"input":0.000059699999999999994,"output":0.0008124,"cacheRead":0.00429696,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00516906}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776177810234,"responseId":"062d8591221920760a3dc411028cf4c3"}}
