{"type":"message","id":"95cfa6b9","parentId":"b3afb829","timestamp":"2026-04-14T14:45:36.110Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Gateway is running fine. Let me now check if there's a way to verify if session-summary hook is loaded and whether I can trigger a test.Actually, let me just check what happens when a new session is created - does the hook fire? Let me also check if there's a way to verify hooks are loaded by checking the gateway's internal state.\n\nActually, looking at this more carefully - the last /new in the commands.log is at 14:23 (2:23 PM), which was BEFORE the current session started at 22:23 (10:23 PM). The current session was started via /new at 22:23, which created a new session at 22:23. So the session-summary hook should have fired at 22:23.\n \nNow I'm examining the commands.log more closely - there are no entries between 14:23 and the current session at 22:23, which means the hook should have fired when the session started. But it's strange that no session-summary file appeared, especially since auto-score-classify did run (evidenced by context.json being updated at 22:44). Both hooks should have the same environment constraints, so this discrepancy is puzzling. Let me check the permissions on the memory directory to see if there's an access issue preventing the summary file from being written.","thinkingSignature":"8c8d2139b157f736004852e0079031bc0ea64fb40adc46988d51aa434d9328d8"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_fe61bf9e6a344799a861de88","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -la ~/.openclaw/workspace/main/memory/ 2>/dev/null; stat ~/.openclaw/workspace/main/memory/ 2>/dev/null | head -5"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":116,"output":329,"cacheRead":74624,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":75069,"cost":{"input":0.0000348,"output":0.0003948,"cacheRead":0.004477439999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.004907039999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp"