{"type":"message","id":"2b41b31c","parentId":"1ec8372a","timestamp":"2026-04-14T14:54:15.466Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Gateway 重启后（pid 从 433541 变成 467116），但 session-summary 文件仍然没有生成。\n\n这意味着问题不是\"gateway 重启加载新代码\"这么简单。\n\n让我 think more carefully about what's actually happening:\n\n1. **session-summary hook fires on `command:new` or `command:reset`** - These events are emitted when the user sends `/new` or `/reset` command\n2. The hook reads from `previousSessionEntry.sessionFile` or searches for it\n3. It reads ephemeral memory, generates a summary, and writes to `memory/`\n\nThe issue might be:\n- The hook IS running (gateway reloaded it)\n- But it's failing SILENTLY because of the async error handling in `run()`\n\n\n- Or the `command:new` event isn't being emitted at all for webchat sessions\n\nI need to trace the event emission path more carefully. When the user sends `/new` from webchat, the commands-reset-hooks module should emit `command:new` and trigger the hook. But if that's not happening, either the event isn't being emitted or the hook itself is silently failing when trying to access session data.\n\nSince the session-summary file still wasn't created after the restart, I should test the `/new` command again to see if the hook fires now that the gateway has reloaded.","thinkingSignature":"c331aed60a24081191f84b85f79595352dae5625498cc9706a9cbfba2f45907e"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nGateway 已重启（pid 467116）。但 session-summary 还是没生成。\n\n来实际触发一次 `/new` 看看 hook 是否跑通：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_c8be4e957b6442ffb47e1001","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 记录当前 session-summary 状态\nls -la ~/.openclaw/workspace/main/memory/*session-summary* 2>/dev/null; echo \"before_new_count: $(ls ~/.openclaw/workspace/main/memory/*session-summary* 2>/dev/null | wc -l)\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":441,"output":389,"cacheRead":76352,"cacheWrite":0,"totalToken