{"type":"message","id":"6aa71e7c","parentId":"23b2ba30","timestamp":"2026-04-14T14:54:26.904Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me send a /new command to the gateway to trigger the session-summary hook. I can do this via the gateway's HTTP API or via a sessions send. Let me try to find how to trigger the command.\n\nActually, I should try to send a /new command to the current session through the gateway's API. But that might be complex. \n\nAlternatively, I can check if there's a way to trigger it via the sessions API. Actually, I think the simplest way is to use the sessions_send tool to send \"/new\" as a message to the current session.\n\nWait, but that's the same as the user doing /new. Let me just check if the hook is properly loaded by doing a simpler test - send a message to the session that would trigger the auto-score-classify hook (which fires on message:preprocessed, which is known to work).\n\nActually, let me try a different approach. Let me just trigger /new through the sessions API if possible.\n\nActually, thinking about it - the commands.log shows /new events from the openclaw-control-ui. The current session (before this /new) was at 14:23. The new gateway restarted at 22:46. Any /new after that would have triggered the hook.\n\nBut there haven't been any /new commands after the restart (commands.log shows the last one at 14:23). So the session-summary hasn't been triggered yet.\n\nLet me try to trigger /new programmatically by sending to the session.","thinkingSignature":"1460a04078788e27dbdfb5a044aeb07ef49ee48a8b884c632265b3b899f6188b"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nGateway 重启后还没有新的 `/new` 触发。让我手动触发一次：\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_51cbf2deed3e4358a025f5a7","name":"sessions_list","arguments":{"activeMinutes":120,"limit":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":190,"output":356,"cacheRead":76736,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":77282,"cost":{"input":0.