{"type":"message","id":"876ec387","parentId":"d025adb4","timestamp":"2026-04-14T14:55:10.209Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Hmm, the session_send timed out. Let me try a different approach - send a message that triggers a /new command more explicitly. Actually wait - I shouldn't use sessions_send to send \"/new\" to a webchat session. That might not be the right approach.\n\nLet me instead try to directly trigger the hook via an HTTP request to the gateway, or better yet, just check if the session-summary file exists now after the SIGUSR1 restart.\n\nActually wait - I should just trigger a new session via the webchat control UI if possible. But I can't do that directly.\n\nLet me check if the /new actually triggered by looking at the commands log.","thinkingSignature":"ea0729122875673c58ed3d872689eac2f494001905143a92cfa8c63ea303ccda"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_6f7b0fe3c57f47aeb92e632c","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"tail -5 ~/.openclaw/logs/commands.log 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":146,"output":174,"cacheRead":77568,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":77888,"cost":{"input":0.0000438,"output":0.00020879999999999998,"cacheRead":0.00465408,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00490668}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776178502479,"responseId":"062d88462efa9e0859ee3ec0897d64c4"}}
