{"type":"message","id":"1f8a51c3","parentId":"46ed1b25","timestamp":"2026-04-14T14:55:26.313Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The /new command didn't appear in commands.log. The sessions_send might not trigger the actual /new command. Let me try a different approach - send a message to the current session and then check if a session-summary was created.Actually, wait - the session_send with \"执行 /new\" may not actually trigger the /new command handler. It just sends a message that looks like \"/new\" to the agent, but the agent interprets it as text, not as a command.\n\nLet me try a different approach. The session is running (status: running). The `/new` command actually needs to be sent through the webchat channel UI, not through sessions_send which just passes it to the agent.\n\nLet me instead just observe and wait for the next real `/new` from the user through the web UI. Or I can check if the session-summary hook works by other means.\n\nActually, let me reconsider. The issue might be that the session-summary hook IS working but the files are being written to a different location. Or maybe the hook runs but there's an error in the handler that's being silently caught.\n\nLet me add some debug logging to understand what's happening. Actually, I can't easily add debug logging without being able to see the gateway logs.\n\nLet me try another approach - check if there's a way to trigger the session-summary hook manually by examining the current session state.\n\nActually, let me just verify by asking the user to do /new through the UI, since I can't trigger it programmatically from here. But first, let me see if the bootstrap hook is working by checking if PREVIOUS_SESSION_SUMMARY.md appears in the current session context somehow.\n\nActually, I just realized - the session-summary hook fires on `command:new` which is emitted when `/new` or `/reset` is received. This happens BEFORE the session is reset. So when I send a message to the session, it doesn't trigger the command hook.\n\nLet me think about what else I can check...\n\nActually, let me try to directly call the hook handler to see if it works. I can import the handler.js and call it directly with a mock event. But this is complex because the handler expects specific event context.\n \nI should check the gateway process itself - maybe the new pid after restart is using a different config file or different hook directories than expected. That could explain why the hook isn't firing even though the process restarted.","thinkingSignature":"ff75493aaf98c32da45fe1ac45618b24a1d499d7b25a7aaa75652d06d6dfbbef"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n`/new` 需要通过 Web UI 手动触发，我这边没法模拟命令。让我换个方式验证——直接测试 hook 代码能不能跑：\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_7019ead5cd1242469dde5f5e","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd ~/.openclaw/hooks/session-summary && node --input-type=module -e \"\nimport handler from './handler.js';\nconst mockEvent = {\n  type: 'command',\n  action: 'new',\n  sessionKey: 'agent:main:test',\n  context: {\n    workspaceDir: '/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main',\n    previousSessionEntry: { sessionId: 'test-id' },\n    sessionEntry: { sessionId: 'new-test-id' },\n    cfg: {}\n  }\n};\nconsole.log('Calling handler...');\nhandler.default ? handler.default(mockEvent) : handler(mockEvent);\nsetTimeout(() => console.log('Done (check memory/)'), 3000);\n\" 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":286,"output":686,"cacheRead":77696,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":78668,"cost":{"input":0.0000858,"output":0.0008232,"cacheRead":0.004661759999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.005570759999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776178510342,"responseId":"062d884e162145efbea324881c4b058e"}}
