{"type":"message","id":"6db32b23","parentId":"e430cbd3","timestamp":"2026-04-14T14:55:35.208Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The handler ran and wrote a summary file! The issue is that the hook fires asynchronously, so `writeSummaryFile` is called but we need to wait a bit. The \"无会话内容\" indicates the session content was empty (no .jsonl file found), which is expected for webchat sessions.\n\nLet me check if the file was actually created and also check if there's a way to confirm the bootstrap hook is working.\n\nThe key insight: **the session-summary hook IS working now after the gateway restart!** It wrote \"2026-04-14-session-summary-无会话内容.md\".\n\nBut wait - this test ran the handler directly, not through the gateway. The question is whether the gateway is actually calling this handler when /new fires. \n\nThe fact that it worked when run directly suggests the code is correct. Let me check if the file was actually created in memory/.","thinkingSignature":"9ff16695ee38a8c6959fb5a2b82558db44f4be1c6d190630441c092144a93b41"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_03d6f44ad20a4fdb9ac012b9","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -la ~/.openclaw/workspace/main/memory/*session-summary* 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":274,"output":222,"cacheRead":77952,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":78448,"cost":{"input":0.00008219999999999999,"output":0.00026639999999999997,"cacheRead":0.00467712,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00502572}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776178528672,"responseId":"062d8860fd7b79273e86a3feb6390460"}}
