{"type":"message","id":"ee1f593e","parentId":"97a42cea","timestamp":"2026-04-14T14:56:01.777Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The environment variable `OPENCLAW_WORKSPACE_DIR` is empty! That means when the gateway runs the hook, it falls back to the default path:\n\n```javascript\nconst memoryRoot = `${workspaceDir}/memory`;\n```\n\nBut `workspaceDir` is empty, so it's joining `/memory` which creates `/memory` absolute path... Actually wait, let me look at the handler again.\n\nIn session-summary handler.js:\n```javascript\nconst MEMORY_DIR = path.join(\n  process.env.OPENCLAW_WORKSPACE_DIR ||\n    path.join(os.homedir(), \".openclaw\", \"workspace\"),\n  \"memory\"\n);\n```\n\nSo if `OPENCLAW_WORKSPACE_DIR` is empty/undefined, it uses `~/.openclaw/workspace/memory`. But the actual workspace is `~/.openclaw/workspace/main/memory`!\n\n\nWhen I tested the handler manually, it successfully wrote to `~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/`, which confirms the gateway's hook is using the wrong directory. I need to check what `workspaceDir` is actually set to in the gateway's event context.","thinkingSignature":"9525b4f8d13eee189888427c44577dce2db0a0a88c019e641371a1228f9b0779"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n问题确认：hook 写入了错误路径。gateway 的 workspaceDir 配置有问题。\n\n检查 gateway 进程环境：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_a26c58e82d90472495fb3404","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /proc/467116/environ 2>/dev/null | tr '\\0' '\\n' | grep -E \"OPENCLAW|WORKSPACE|HOOK\" | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":281,"output":309,"cacheRead":78336,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":78926,"cost":{"input":0.0000843,"output":0.00037079999999999996,"cacheRead":0.004700159999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.005155259999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776178554161,"responseId":"062d8879da3d30a54610f80e2a08a42f"}}
