{"type":"message","id":"a70cbe46","parentId":"bc140525","timestamp":"2026-04-14T15:04:12.836Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, the file was moved but it still doesn't show up in the filter! Let me check why:\n\n```javascript\nconst summaryFiles = files.filter(f => f.endsWith('-session-summary.md'));\n```\n\nThe file is `2026-04-14-session-summary-verify.md`. It ends with `-verify.md`, not `-session-summary.md`.\n\nThe filter checks for files ending with exactly `-session-summary.md`. But session-summary files created by the hook are named `2026-04-14-session-summary-{slug}.md` where `{slug}` is after the last `-session-summary`.\n\nWait - the HOOK.md says files should be named `YYYY-MM-DD-session-summary-{slug}.md`. \n\nSo the actual filename format is `2026-04-14-session-summary-{slug}.md`, which means the string `-session-summary` appears twice in the full path. I need to verify whether my filter is correctly identifying files with this pattern or if there's an issue with how the hook is generating these filenames in the first place.","thinkingSignature":"d731927f2875032c268159c81ec96abc89c6eb142dc4ed82bad2abd6e626f34b"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_6a4b180772c14e33b4ac25dd","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls ~/.openclaw/workspace/main/memory/2026-04-14-session-summary* 2>/dev/null\necho \"---check what session-summary hook actually creates---\"\ngrep -n \"filename.*session.summary\\|session.summary.*filename\\|writeSummaryFile\" ~/.openclaw/hooks/session-summary/handler.js 2>/dev/null | head -10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":150,"output":308,"cacheRead":84672,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":85130,"cost":{"input":0.000044999999999999996,"output":0.0003696,"cacheRead":0.005080319999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0054949199999999995}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776179045976,"responseId":"062d8a6544ecfdca2388e33a091d6d9f"}}
